"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Volvidion\",\"content\":\"Volvidon, slightly larger than an Aptonoth, is covered in red segmented armor plates, allowing it to curl into a ball. It features an exceptionally long, chameleon-like tongue covered in sticky saliva.\\n\\nVolvidon spits paralyzing liquid, inflicts Soiling with a foul odor, and uses attacks similar to Arzuros and Lagombi. Its long tongue pulls prey, and it can roll into a ball to crush foes during combat.\\n\\nVolvidon generally avoids trouble but can be aggressive when cornered. It's an insectivore, using its long, sticky tongue to feed on Neopterons.\\n\\nElements:\\nAilments: Paralysis, Soiled\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 613 cm - 892 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":42,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":42,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":44,\"keys\":[\"The Limb Reaper\",\"Goss Harag\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Goss Harag\",\"content\":\"Goss Harag (Also called \\\"The Limb Reaper\\\"), a large Fanged Beast, combines bear and Namahage features with shaggy white and brown fur. Its pale blue armor turns red when agitated, and it has bright yellow eyes. The head features round ears, a leaf-shaped snout, and four short ice-like horns. Forelegs have longer digits, while bear-like feet adorn the hindlegs. Goss Harag moves both quadrupedally and bipedally, using knuckle-walking with curled foreleg digits.\\n\\nGoss Harag, physically robust and adapted to harsh cold environments, uses strong forearms and body weight for powerful attacks, causing shock waves or tremors. Despite its bulk, it can leap great distances and achieve sudden bursts of speed. By inhaling cold air, it freezes bodily fluids, creating icy blasts and forming deadly blades and bludgeons. Goss Harag, an aggressive apex predator, dominates icy territories, hunting smaller creatures and fiercely defending its turf against challengers.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 643 cm - 906 cm / Height: Large\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":43,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":43,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":45,\"keys\":[\"Palamute\",\"Canyne\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Canyne\",\"content\":\"Canynes are Fanged Beasts with a dog-like appearance, displaying a wide range of colors, ear and tail shapes, and markings that vary individually.\\n\\nCanynes exhibit high-speed movement, great leaps, and the ability to climb steep slopes. In Kamura Village, some Canynes, known as \\\"Palamutes,\\\" are trained as Hunting Buddies akin to Felynes. Intelligent and responsive to orders, Canynes can use specially designed weapons and carry a hunter on their back without compromising speed. Like Felynes, they often wear armor tailored to their anatomy for field excursions.\\n\\nHeight: Small\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":44,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":44,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":46,\"keys\":[\"Bombadgy\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Bombadgy\",\"content\":\"\\nBombadgy looks like an overweight badger or raccoon with gray, flabby skin, long tendrils for eyebrows, and jagged rows along its back and sides. Its legs have scales and end in five-digit claws.\\n\\nBombadgy is usually non-aggressive but defends itself by releasing flammable gas that causes an explosive reaction when expelled, turning it into a living bomb.\\n\\nSize: Small\\nFanged Beast\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":45,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":45,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":47,\"keys\":[\"Kecha Wacha\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kecha Wacha\",\"content\":\"Kecha Wacha is a lemur-like monster with long arms, hook-like fingers, bright yellow fur, blue skin, and a tube-like trunk. It can fold its spiked ears over its face for intimidation.\\n\\nKecha Wacha shoots mucus from its trunk-like nose to cause Waterblight. It can glide using a membrane, resembling a flying squirrel, making it one of the few Fanged Beasts capable of \\\"flying.\\\"\\n\\nCurious in nature Kecha Wacha will investigate anything in their environment that is new to them. As relatively peaceful monsters these creatures would rather flee than fight, yet if fleeing is not an option they can be surprisingly aggressive and will readily use their long, sharp, and hooked claws, trunk-like nose and mask-like ears to defend themselves.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 779 cm - 1019 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":46,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":46,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":48,\"keys\":[\"Ash Kecha Wacha\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ash Kecha Wacha\",\"content\":\"Unlike the bright orange of the normal species, this variant has a washed blueish fur with black coloration on the hands, feet, and head. The mask on its ears has a yellow-orange pattern against a dark background.\\n\\nThis subspecies seems to be able to spit flaming projectiles at its foes, rather than the watery globules of its common counterpart.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 779 cm - 1329 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":47,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":47,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":49,\"keys\":[\"Bishaten\",\"Frenetic Ascetic\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Bishaten \",\"content\":\"Bishaten (also known as: \\\"Frenetic Ascetic\\\"), a unique Fanged Beast, has cream and blue fur, wing-like patagia on its arms, and a strong tail serving as a fifth limb. Its face features bony protrusions, a beak-like structure on both jaws, and large ears. The mane on its neck is more prominent in males. Bishaten stores fruits in a belly pouch.\\n\\nBishaten, an omnivorous monster with a preference for fruits, stores them in its belly pouch. Highly acrobatic, it performs spinning moves, stands on its tail, and uses its wings to glide. Bishaten enjoys pranks and can throw fruits, causing poisoning or stunning effects.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Stun, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 832 cm - 1054 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":48,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":48,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":50,\"keys\":[\"Dismal Jester\",\"Blood Orange Bishaten\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Blood Orange Bishaten\",\"content\":\"Blood Orange Bishaten (Also known as: \\\"Dismal Jester\\\")  shares a resemblance with the standard Bishaten but features orange and black feathers, yellow wing tips, and white sections on its face, legs, and tail.\\n\\nBlood Orange Bishaten differs by breathing fire and tossing explosive pinecones, either igniting them with fire breath or impact force. It adeptly spins these as weapons or sets them as ground mines.\\n\\nBlood Orange Bishaten is an aggressive monster, capable of retaliating with fire moves when provoked. It enjoys attacking other Bishaten and can hold its ground against formidable foes like Almudron but faces competition from creatures like Rathalos and Chaotic Gore Magala.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Stun, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 832 cm - 1054 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":49,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":49,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":51,\"keys\":[\"Garangolm\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Garangolm\",\"content\":\"Garangolm is a colossal Fanged Beast with a crown-like shell on its back and head, resembling a gorilla. It has a long tail with prongs.\\n\\nGarangolm, a powerful Fanged Beast, emits sap-like fluid to encourage plant growth on its body. When enraged, it transforms its arms into gauntlet-like masses—right arm with semi-molten rock, left arm with mossy growths. As its health drops, it covers both arms with more molten rock and moss, gaining new attacks.\\n\\nGarangolm is peaceful unless attacked, escalating aggression with strength. It engages in territorial battles, facing formidable monsters like Lunagaron in Turf Wars.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element, Water Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Blastblight, Waterblight, Iceblight\\nWeakness: None (Normal State), Thunder element, Fire Element (Mossy Arm), Ice Element, Water Element (Molten Arm)\\nLength: 1529 cm - 1789 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Beast\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":50,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":50,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":f