ns and monsters. They travel in groups, and when threatened, others flee for safety while the alpha male may attempt to fight back before eventually fleeing.\\n\\nLength: ~1002 cm \\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":52,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":52,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":54,\"keys\":[\"Apceros\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apceros\",\"content\":\"Apceros are herbivorous reptiles found in desert and volcanic regions. Resembling tortoises, they possess protective shells and mace-like tails with sharp spikes.\\n\\nApceros attack with headbutts and spiked tails, and they are notorious for surrounding and restricting the movement of their targets.\\n\\nAggressive by nature, Apceros attack intruders on sight, collaborating in small herds to eliminate threats without concern for larger monsters nearby.\\n\\nLength: ~ 988 cm / Height: Medium\\nOrnithischia\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":53,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\