atch_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":64,\"keys\":[\"Rathalos\",\"King of the Skies\",\"Fire Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rathalos\",\"content\":\"Rathalos are formidable, bipedal wyverns with vibrant red and black markings. They possess a flame sac for breathing fire, poisonous talons, and a spiked club at the end of their long tail. Ornate wing patterns suggest a role in attracting mates. Known for their aggressive nature, Rathalos are powerful predators with deadly ranged and melee attacks.\\n\\nRegular Rathalos' will only mate with reagular Rathians. Rathalos' and Rathians mate for life.\\n\\nRathalos are adept flyers, executing surprise aerial attacks with poisonous talons or fiery projectiles. On the ground, their powerful legs allow them to chase and inflict damage, while their clubbed tail and sharp teeth add to their formidable offensive capabilities. Some Rathalos can also stay airborne for brief fireball assaults.\\n\\nRathalos are territorial and aggressive hunters, using aerial tactics to stalk and swoop down on prey. After a successful kill, they carry it away to consume in a secluded area, avoiding potential theft from scavengers or rival monsters.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Stun, Poison\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Water Element, Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1140 cm - 2248 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":63,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":63,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":65,\"keys\":[\"Azure Fire Wyvern\",\"Azure Rathalos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Azure Rathalos\",\"content\":\"Azure Rathalos, a Rathalos Subspecies, distinguishes itself with an azure-colored shell, lime green wing webbing, and a single red spike on its tail. It possesses increased stamina, health, and attack power compared to its counterpart, displaying heightened aggression in battle.\\n\\nAzure Rathalos' will only mate with Pink Rathians. Azure Rathalos' and Pink Rathians mate for life.\\n\\nAzure Rathalos, a subspecies of Rathalos, exhibits heightened aggression, stamina, health, and attack power. Its azure-colored shell, lime green wing webbing, and increased aerial prowess make it a formidable adversary, though it generally avoids larger threats beyond its territory.\\n\\nAzure Rathalos are particularly aggressive and intelligent, especially during mating season, intensifying territorial disputes and competition for prime hunting grounds.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Stun, Poison\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Water Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 1140 cm - 2248 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":64,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":64,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":66,\"keys\":[\"Black Flame King\",\"Darkness Lord\",\"Dreadking\",\"Dreadking Rathalos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Dreadking Rathalos\",\"content\":\"Dreadking Rathalos (Also called: \\\"Dreadking\\\", \\\"Darkness Lord\\\", \\\"Black Flame King\\\") closely resembles normal Rathalos but is larger with thicker features. It has a crimson hue, iridescent black plating, and dark brown wings with cream-colored markings.\\n\\nDreadking Rathalos' will only mate with Dreadqueen Rathians. Dreadking Rathalos' and Dreadqueen Rathians mate for life.\\n\\nDreadking Rathalos shares movesets with Rathalos but introduces new attacks, such as ground-explosive fireballs that cause lingering damage. Their venomous talons now carry Noxious Poison. They gain the ability to shoot three fireballs simultaneously.\\n\\nDreadking Rathalos are formidable monsters known for their destructive fireballs, and hunters need a special permit to engage them.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1954 cm - 2263 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":65,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"positi