ilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":66,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":68,\"keys\":[\"Apex Rathalos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apex Rathalos\",\"content\":\"Apex Rathalos shares similarities with Dreadking Rathalos, featuring red scars on its body. Notably, its neck glows orange when preparing to breathe fire or roar.\\n\\nApex Rathalos' will only mate with Apex Rathians. Apex Rathalos' and Apex Rathians mate for life.\\n\\nApex Rathalos is highly aggressive, using powerful claw attacks and large, explosive fireballs. Its enraged state involves launching massive fireballs from the sky, creating a dangerous area effect.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Poison\\nLength: 1954 cm - 2263 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":67,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":67,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":69,\"keys\":[\"Female Fire Wyvern\",\"Rathian\",\"Queen of the Land\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rathian\",\"content\":\"Rathian, (Also called: \\\"Female Fire Wyvern\\\", \\\"Queen of the Land\\\") a medium-sized true flying wyvern, has a dull, muted green hide with a long chin spike. Unlike Rathalos, she features a moss-like fur on her upper back and wingtips. Her clubbed tail lacks spikes but is equipped with sharp, poisonous needles.\\n\\nRegular Rathians will only mate with regular Rathalos. There are rumours, that Rathians sometimes \\\"mate\\\" with male Seregios and it is joked, that the first Yian Garuga has been born after a Rathian mated with a Yian Kut Ku and bore offspring. Rathians and Rathalos' mate for life.\\n\\nRathian, similar to Rathalos, can produce flaming projectiles and release potent fire blasts. She uses poisonous barbs on her tail club to inflict blunt-force, toxic wounds. With powerful legs, she can run at high speeds, and keen vision requires tactics like Flash Bombs in combat.\\n\\nRathian is territorial, patrolling from the ground, while her Rathalos mate patrols the sky. She aggressively defends her nest and becomes hostile to potential threats, particularly hunters carrying her eggs.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Poison\\nLength: 1151 cm - 2303 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":68,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":68,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":70,\"keys\":[\"Cherry Blossom Fire Wyvern\",\"Pink Rathian\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Pink Rathian\",\"content\":\"Pink Rathian (Also called: \\\"Cherry Blossom Fire Wyvern\\\") has a heavily-armored body, boasting greater health and attack power than the green Rathian. She is frequently encountered in quests alongside her male counterpart, the Azure Rathalos.\\n\\nPink Rathians will only mate with with Azure Rathalos'. Pink Rathians and Azure Rathalos' mate for life.\\n\\nHer attacks are generally stronger than those of normal Rathian, they are also much faster than its green relative, but that aside the two are identical in many ways.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Poison, Water Element\\nLength: 1151 cm - 2303 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":69,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":69,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":71,\"keys\":[\"Deadly Princess\",\"Dreadqueen Rathian\",\"Violet Poison Princess\",\"Dreadqueen\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Flying Wyvern\",\"Rathian\",\"Apex Rathian\",\"Gold Rathian\",\"Medium Monster\",\"Pink Rathian\"],\"comment\":\"Dreadqueen Rathian\",\"content\":\"Dreadqueen Rathian (Also Called: \\\"Dreadqueen\\\", \\\"Deadly Princess\\\", \\\"Violet Poison Princess\\\") is larger than the normal Rathian and has a purple tint on her scales, with poison visibly emanating from her tail during attacks.\\n\\nDreadqueen Rathian will only mate with Dreadking Rathalos'. Dreadqueen Rathians and Dreadking Rathalos' mate for life.\\n\\nDreadqueen Rathian uses her poisonous tail to attack hunters, inflicting poison or more severe variants. In enraged states, she may perform aerial attacks by flying high and diving onto targets while using her poisonous tail.\\n\\nDreadqueen Rathian is highly aggressive and territorial, posing a greater threat than normal Rathian. Hunters need a special permit to confront these monsters due to their extreme aggression and lethal attacks.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison, deadly poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Poison\\nLength: 1973 cm - 2261 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":70,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":70,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":72,\"keys\":[\"Golden Moon\",\"Goldian\",\"Gold Rathian\",\"Gold Fire Wyvern\",\"Illustrious Queen\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gold Rathian\",\"content\":\"Gold Rathian (Also Called: \\\"Goldian\\\", \\\"Gold Fire Wyvern\\\", \\\"Golden Moon\\\", \\\"Illustrious Queen\\\") is protected by a sturdy golden shell that repels attacks, making it a formidable foe.\\n\\nGold Rathian will only mate with Silver Rathalos'. Gold Rathians and Silver Rathalos' mate for life.\\n\\nGold Rathian is vulnerable to Thunder Element attacks. It possesses enhanced control over its flame sac, allowing for more ferocious fireball attacks. It can also enter an Incandescent state, increasing the aggressiveness of its moves.\\n\\nGold Rathian's heightened aggression is likely a survival adaptation, helping it fend off threats and establish dominance in its territory.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Poison\\nLength: 1151 cm - 2303 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":71,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":71,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":73,\"keys\":[],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apex Rathian\",\"content\":\"Apex Rathian shares similarities with Dreadqueen Rathian, featuring red scars, sharp teeth, and enlarged spikes on wings, legs, and tail. The eyes and scars glow bright red when enraged.\\n\\nApex Rathians will only mate with with Apex Rathalos'. Apex Rathians and Apex Rathalos' mate for life.\\n\\nApex Rathian is brutal, aggressive, and attacks anything on sight. She has similar attacks to normal Rathian but with alterations, including impaling poisonous spikes on the ground. When enraged, she performs a dangerous triple tail swipe attack with heavy damage and multiple spikes.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison, deadly poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Poison\\nLength: 1973 cm - 2261 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":72,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":72,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":74,\"keys\":[\"Basarios\",\"Bellowing Boulder\",\"Rock Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Basarios\",\"content\":\"Basarios (Also Called: \\\"Rock Wyvern\\\", \\\"Bellowing Boulder\\\"), the young form of Gravios, has a hard, rocky carapace that provides protection and camouflage. Despite having wings, it moves slowly and can only fly briefly due to its weight.\\n\\nBasarios has the ability to release sleeping or poisonous gas, rare fire plumes, and a powerful lava beam. It can also throw fireballs and has the capability to burrow underground, resembling a large gray rock for camouflage. Basarios eats rock and minerals for nutrients. \\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison, Sleep\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element\\nLength: 1154 cm - 1754 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":73,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":73,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":75,\"keys\":[\"Ruby Basarios\",\"Peach Rock Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ruby Basarios\",\"content\":\"The Ruby Basarios (Also Called: \\\"Peach Rock Wyvern\\\" is distinguished by pink crystals protruding from its back and a moss-covered body, indicating a varied diet and a habitat rich in vegetation.\\n\\nIts shell is highly resistant to damage and is difficult to penetrate. It is capable of launching crystals from its back by shaking its body back and forth.\\n\\nThe Ruby Basarios, similar to the common Basarios, remains camouflaged as a rock when buried in the earth. It generally avoids aggression unless disturbed directly. Ruby Basarios eats rock and minerals for nutrients. \\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Poison, Noxious Poison, Sleep, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1269 cm - 1783 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":74,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":74,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":76,\"keys\":[\"Armor Wyvern\",\"Gravios\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gravios\",\"content\":\"Gravios (Also Called: \\\"Armor Wyvern\\\") boasts a dense, stone-like armored shell that shields it from physical harm. Its immense size and weight restrict its flight, though it has large wings. The creature wields a thick, club-like tail.\\n\\nGravios lacks the poisonous gas of its juvenile form, Basarios, but emits a potent sleeping gas from its underside. This, along with its formidable shell, serves as a deterrent against predators. Gravios can also release flammable gas as a byproduct of its diet and 'heat beam.'\\n\\nGravios is territorial and resides in the Volcano, where it nurtures and protects its young Basarios. It is typically docile but becomes aggressive when provoked. Gravios eats rock and minerals for nutrients. \\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1049 cm - 3065 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":75,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":75,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":77,\"keys\":[\"Black Gravios\",\"Black Armor Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Black Gravios\",\"content\":\"Black Gravios is essentially a Gravios with a unique black hide and red spines caused by elevated body temperature. It's larger and heavier than the standard Gravios.\\n\\nBlack Gravios is more proficient in the use of its heat beam, thanks to its sturdier body.\\n\\nFar more aggressive than its grey counterpart, the Black Gravios will attack on sight. It will more commonly expel explosive gas than sleep gas. Black Gravios eats rock and minerals for nutrients. \\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1946 cm - 3065 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":76,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":76,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":78,\"keys\":[\"Monoblos\",\"One Horned Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Monoblos\",\"content\":\"Monoblos are large wyverns resembling Diablos but with only one horn on their nose, with a rock-hard carapace, Ceratopsian-like head, and a mace-shaped tail club adorned with spikes. They have a frill on the back of their head and various spikes on their body. When enraged, the frill gains red markings.\\n\\nMonoblos are powerful wyverns with a lethal roar. They use horn-thrusts, tail-swings, and sand-tunneling as their main forms of attack.\\n\\nMonoblos are aggressive creatures that attack hunters on sight. When enraged, their crown becomes inflamed with red streaks, making them faster and more powerful.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 1683 cm - 2918 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":77,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":77,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":79,\"keys\":[\"White One Horned Wyvern\",\"White Monoblos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"White Monoblos\",\"content\":\"White Monoblos features a bright white carapace with a frill that becomes more strikingly flushed with blood when enraged. It shares the same body structure as the common species.\\n\\nWhite Monoblos behaves similarly to the common species, frequently moving underground when not engaged with a hunter, making it challenging to track.\\n\\nThe shell of White Monoblos is harder than that of a normal Monoblos, thus increasing its defense.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 1849 cm - 2810 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":78,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":78,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":80,\"keys\":[\"Tyrant of the Desert\",\"Horned Wyvern\",\"Diablos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Diablos\",\"content\":\"Diablos (Also Called: \\\"Horned Wyvern\\\", \\\"Tyrant of the Desert\\\") are formidable, bipedal wyverns with powerful armor plating, massive bull-like horns, and a spiked tail club. Their appearance is accentuated by tusk-like fangs and a large neck frill. Diablos are known for their powerful attacks and are equipped with sturdy wings despite being flightless.\\n\\nDiablos can burrow underground and surprise enemies, employing powerful roars and charging attacks with their horns. Their ability to run at high speeds makes them formidable adversaries in battle.\\n\\nDiablos are herbivores that feed on desert cacti. Despite their herbivorous diet, they are highly aggressive and territorial, using their powerful horns as weapons. Diablos are known to engage in battles for territory or mating rights with other individuals. Their wings are primarily used for escaping when trapped in the sand, as their massive mass limits their ability to fly for extended periods.\\n\\nIf a Diablos looses one or both it's horns during a battle and survives, it looses any mating rights and is no longer attractive for female Diablos. Very rarely, the broken horns of a Diablos can regrow and often leads to the creation of a Bloodbath Diablos.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1796 cm - 3030 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":79,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":79,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":81,\"keys\":[\"Black Horn Wyvern of the Desert\",\"Black Diablos\",\"Black Horn\",\"Tyrantess of the Desert\",\"Black Horn Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Black Diablos\",\"content\":\"Black Diablos (Also called: \\\"Black Horn Wyvern\\\", \\\"Black Horn\\\", \\\"Tyrantess of the Desert\\\", \\\"Black Horn Wyvern of the Desert\\\") are not a true subspecies but rather female Diablos in heat. During mating season, their shell turns black as a warning sign of heightened aggression and hostility. It's important to note that Black Diablos cannot be male.\\n\\nExtremely aggressive, Diablos are among the most hostile creatures in the Desert. They use sand as cover for devastating ambushes and are known for launching aggressive attacks on intruders approaching their territory. Black Diablos, in particular, behaves similarly to normal Diablos and is highly territorial, attacking other monsters like Tigrex if they enter her domain.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1865 cm - 2930 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":80,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":80,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":82,\"keys\":[\"Bloodbath Diablos\",\"Bloodbath\",\"Massacre Demon\",\"Horns of Fury\",\"Roars of Rage\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Bloodbath Diablos\",\"content\":\"Bloodbath Diablos, with a deformed horn and enlarged counterpart, features bluish blood on its face, wings, and tail. The unique horn growth occurs after the loss of one horn.\\n\\n\\nBloodbath Diablos is more powerful and aggressive than a regular Diablos. It can charge quickly, causing devastating damage. When enraged, red flame-shaped veins appear on its body and in its heightened enraged state, it produces a steam explosion, pushing away nearby foes and enabling directional changes during a charge.\\n\\nBloodbath Diablos is exceptionally aggressive, especially towards hunters, behaving more rogue-like when confronted by threats, likely because its horns have been broken by a hunter. \\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 2288 cm - 2770 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":81,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":81,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":83,\"keys\":[\"Apex Diablos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apex Diablos\",\"content\":\"Apex Diablos closely resembles a Bloodbath Diablos but with normal, unbroken horns, with a darker and bloodier color scheme, larger horns, and prominent scars that brighten when enraged or attacking.\\n\\nApex Diablos is extremely brutal and aggressive, attacking anything on sight with powerful moves, including a devastating charge, a damaging spin, and the ability to charge mid-roar. They are known to engage in battles with each other.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: None\\nLength: 2288 cm - 2770 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":82,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":82,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":84,\"keys\":[\"Thunderous Rage\",\"Thunder Wyvern\",\"Astalos\",\"Electric Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Astalos\",\"content\":\"Astalos (Also called: \\\"Electric Wyvern\\\", \\\"Thunder Wyvern\\\", \\\"Thunderous Rage\\\") has a predominantly sharp, dark green plated body with a bright-colored underside. Its wings resemble those of a Glasswing butterfly, and its tail features two pairs of pincers at the tip. The monster's head is relatively small with a large horn, and its eyes change from red to green when charged.\\n\\nAstalos generates green electricity by moving and rubbing its body parts, releasing it from its wings, tail, and horn. It uses sharp-winged dive-bombing attacks, paralyzes with its tail, and breathes electricity. Astalos is hyper-aggressive, attacking anything on sight, even picking fights with other monsters without apparent reason.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Water Element\\nLength: 2288 cm - 2770 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":83,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":83,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":85,\"keys\":[\"Lightning Revolt\",\"Boltreaver\",\"Boltreaver Astalos\",\"Blue Thunder Lord\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Boltreaver Astalos\",\"content\":\"Boltreaver Astalos (Also Called: Boltreaver, \\\"Lightning Revolt\\\", \\\"Blue Thunder Lord\\\") has a turquoise tint, larger wing claws, tail pincers, and head crest. It can charge further, changing its electricity color from green to blue.\\n\\nBoltreaver Astalos has a larger charge capacity, can supercharge itself, and manipulate electromagnetism to generate a blade-like beam of electricity.\\n\\nBoltreaver Astalos are highly aggressive, attacking relentlessly even when foes are out of sight. Hunters need a special permit to hunt them.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Water Element\\nLength: 2108 cm - 2441 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":84,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":84,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":86,\"keys\":[\"Paolumu\",\"Floating Sky Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Paolumu\",\"content\":\"Paolumu (Also called: \\\"Floating Sky Wyvery\\\")is a bat-like wyvern that slightly resembles the Honduran white bat, covered in white fur with pink facial features. It has pinkish-brown scales on its back, underbelly, and tail. With rodent-like buck teeth, it feeds on coral eggs. Using powerful breathing it can inflate its neckpouch and allow it to float like a balloon.\\n\\nPaolumu has a unique air sac in its neck that allows it to float like a balloon after inhaling air. While floating, it attacks with its tail and breathes wind. Paolumu is generally calm unless provoked, becoming aggressive when threatened. It won't attack hunters unless provoked first and faces competition from other monsters in the Coral Highlands.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1006 cm - 1429 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":85,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":85,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":87,\"keys\":[\"Nightshade Paolumu\",\"Floating Sleep Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Flying Wyvern\",\"Paolumu\",\"Medium Monster\"],\"comment\":\"Nightshade Paolumu\",\"content\":\"Nightshade Paolumu (Also called: \\\"Floating Sleep Wyvern\\\") is a bat-like Flying Wyvern with dark fur, a white face, and peacock-like patterns on its neck. It has a unique air sac that allows it to float in the air. It is generally calm but becomes aggressive when provoked.\\n\\nNightshade Paolumu is more aggressive than Paolumu and excels in aerial combat. It can quickly inflate itself, fly at high speeds, and release sleep-inducing gas.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1006 cm - 1406 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":86,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":86,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":88,\"keys\":[\"Wind Drifting Wyvern\",\"Legiana\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Legiana\",\"content\":\"Legiana (Also called: \\\"Wind Drifting Wyvern\\\") is a sleek Flying Wyvern with beige and navy-blue colors, leaf-like wingtips, and striped patterns on its body. It possesses antenna-like fins on its head. It has a membrane that allows it to move swiftly and emit chilling winds. With bright yellow eyes, powerful legs, and piercing talons, Legiana is a formidable creature. The distinct features include its dark navy blue face, tail, feet, and wingtips, as well as retractable fins on its tail and star-like shapes on its wings.\\n\\nLegiana emits a chilling wind, making prey vulnerable. It's highly agile, snatching prey from the air and using strong legs to throw monsters like Paolumu. Fiercely territorial, it guards its territory.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Ice Blight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1495 cm - 2124 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":87,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":87,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":89,\"keys\":[\"Wind Drifting Wyvern\",\"Legiana\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Large Monster\",\"Flying Wyvern\",\"Legiana\"],\"comment\":\"Shrieking Legiana\",\"content\":\"Shrieking Legiana (Alco called: \\\"Wind Drifting Wyvern\\\") share the same structure as regular Legiana but have black coloration with icy spikes on the chest, tail, and wings.\\n\\nShrieking Legiana has enhanced ice manipulation, covering large areas with ice spikes and executing powerful dive attacks, adapting to the Hoarfrost Reach.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Ice Blight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1429 cm - 2252 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":88,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":88,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":90,\"keys\":[\"Bagelgoose\",\"Party Crasher\",\"Beetlejuice\",\"The Invading Tyrant\",\"Explosive Scale Wyvern\",\"Bazelgeuse\",\"Bomber Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Bazelgeuse\",\"content\":\"Bazelgeuse (Also called: \\\"Explosive Scale Wyvern\\\", \\\"Party Crasher\\\", \\\"Bomber Wyvern\\\", \\\"The Invading Tyrant\\\" or mockingly called: \\\"Bagelgoose\\\", \\\"Beetlejuice\\\"), is a large Flying Wyvern with thick, bronze-sheened scales. It has a bulky upper body, large wingspan, and occasionally enters a \\\"superheated\\\" state, making its scales glow red hot.\\n\\nBazelgeuse uses its explosive scales offensively, dislodging them as explosive traps. In a superheated state, these scales explode rapidly. It can release a short-range fire blast and use powerful tackles. Aggressive and territorial, Bazelgeuse seeks out targets, often interrupting other monster battles, and engages in turf wars, particularly with Deviljho.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblast, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 1696 cm - 2410 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":89,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":89,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":91,\"keys\":[\"Party Crasher\",\"Seething Bagelgoose\",\"Seething Bazelgeuse\",\"Great Calamity\",\"The Invading Tyrant\",\"Death from Above\",\"Explosive Scale Wyvern\",\"Seething Beetlejuice\",\"Bomber Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Seething Bazelgeuse\",\"content\":\"Seething Bazelgeuse (Also called: \\\"Explosive Scale Wyvern\\\", \\\"Party Crasher\\\", \\\"Bomber Wyvern\\\", \\\"The Invading Tyrant\\\", \\\"Death from Above\\\", \\\"Great Calamity\\\" or mockingly called: \\\"Seething Bagelgoose\\\", \\\"Seething Beetlejuice\\\") has a metallic blue coloration in its normal state, resembling Bazelgeuse's heated state. It can further power up, with its head and tail glowing white-hot and then searing purple-white.\\n\\nSeething Bazelgeuse has enhanced its explosive scales, dropping them over a wider range. In its second powered-up state, the scales glow purple-hot before causing a massive explosion. When all scales glow purple, it performs a devastating move by soaring into the sky, scattering scales, and crashing back down with a huge explosion, using up all scales and reverting to its regular state. Seething Bazelgeuse can fling scales without needing bombing runs, making them more unpredictable.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblast, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1696 cm - 2410 cm / Height: Large\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":90,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":90,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":92,\"keys\":[\"Blank Stare\",\"Khezu\",\"Strange Wyvern\",\"Charging Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Khezu\",\"content\":\"Khezu are meduim sized, pale wyverns with damp, rubbery skin resembling amphibians. They have visible blood vessels, a specialized tail orifice for electrical attacks, and suction pad-like toes for climbing. With regressed eyes, they rely on a keen sense of smell. Hermaphroditic, Khezu reproduce by injecting paralyzing Whelps into prey, which grow inside until ready to leave.\\n\\nKhezu, cave dwellers, venture outside when needed or when food is scarce. They are vulnerable to larger wyverns like Tigrex outside, but inside caves, they have an advantage, being unhampered by darkness and able to attack from the ceiling.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis, Stun\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 436 cm - 1225 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":91,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":91,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":93,\"keys\":[\"Red Khezu\",\"Charging Wyvern\",\"Red Strange Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Red Khezu\",\"content\":\"The Red Khezu has a blood-red hide, enhanced control over its extendable neck, and a more potent thunder sac compared to the common species.\\n\\nThe Red Khezu (Also Called: \\\"Charging Wyvern\\\", \\\"Red Strange Wyvern\\\") shares behavior with the common Khezu but has a unique neck-thrusting attack. Notably, it is immune to Fire and weak to Water, in contrast to the standard Khezu.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis,\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 436 cm - 1205 cm / Height: ~ tank size\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":92,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":92,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":94,\"keys\":[\"Gigginox\",\"Creeping Venom Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gigginox\",\"content\":\"Gigginox (Also Called: \\\"Creeping Venom Wyvern\\\"), like Khezu, is a blind, cave-dwelling wyvern. It detects prey using a special organ that senses body heat rather than smell. Unlike Khezu, Gigginox has a wide and flat body, lacks visible veins, and is more agile and faster, utilizing all four limbs and its tail for movement. Gigginox has an elastic neck and tail, which can stretch for attacks. Its color changes when enraged, and it has a circular, leech-like mouth with sharp teeth.\\n\\nGigginox can cling to cave ceilings and has a unique attack where it drags hunters underneath itself. It can spit or release poison gas from pores, lay Giggi Sacs that spawn young Giggis, and excrete poisonous clouds. Experienced hunters can distinguish between the types of globs Gigginox produces.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 982 cm - 1266 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":93,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":93,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"dela