on\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":96,\"keys\":[],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Giggi\",\"content\":\"Giggi are featureless creatures spawned from large organic globules known as \\\"Giggi Sacs\\\" within dark caves. They have grey bodies with purple markings, small stubby arms, and round mouths with small yet sharp teeth, which they use to drain the bodily fluids of their victims.\\n\\nGiggi are small creatures that can produce a weak poison. To nourish themselves and grow, they leech onto and drain the blood of other beings, including hunters.\\n\\nThey are tiny, about the size of a regular housecat.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":95,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":95,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":97,\"keys\":[\"Nargacuga\",\"Swift Wyvern\",\"Pouncing Shadow\",\"Red Glare in the Darkness\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nargacuga\",\"content\":\"Nargacuga (Also Called: \\\"Swift Wyvern\\\", \\\"Red Glare in the Darkness\\\", \\\"Pouncing Shadow\\\") has black scales, fur, and red eyes, resembling a predatory black panther. In Rage Mode, its eyes glow red, and its tail erects large spikes. The tail is flexible, prehensile, and produces rattling sounds similar to a rattlesnake.\\n\\nNargacuga is a versatile attacker, utilizing its bladed wings, sharp tail, and biting capabilities in battle. Its tail spikes become more prominent in Rage Mode, adding to its offensive arsenal. Additionally, Nargacuga possesses strong muscles, allowing it to perform high-speed jumps over long distances and heights.\\n\\nNargacuga, a stealthy and cautious monster, resides in high trees in dark, hard-to-reach locations, making it difficult for hunters to approach without detection.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Bleeding\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 1602 cm - 2355 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":96,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":96,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":98,\"keys\":[\"Green Nargacuga\",\"Green Swift Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Green Nargacuga\",\"content\":\"This Green Nargacuga (Also called: \\\"Green Swift Wyvern\\\") is covered in mossy green fur. Its long, prehensile tail ends in a bright red spike, and its eyes are a bright yellow.\\n\\nThe Green Nargacuga showcases advanced moves, especially when enraged, including a stunning tail slam and subsequent jump and smash attack.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Stun\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 1410 cm - 2002 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":97,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":97,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":99,\"keys\":[\"Moonlit Shadow\",\"Lucent Nargacuga\",\"Moon Swift Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lucent Nargacuga\",\"content\":\"Lucent Nargacuga (Alco called: \\\"Moon Swift Wyvern\\\", \\\"Moonlit Shadow\\\") has metallic, azure scales, patches of white fur, and a golden-colored chest.\\n\\nLucent Nargacuga, also known as the Moon Swift Wyvern, possesses the ability to turn invisible and performs a double tail slam similar to its green relative. It can extend its spikes by shaking its tail, releasing venomous spikes during its attacks.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 1410 cm - 2002 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":98,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":98,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":100,\"keys\":[\"Wind Cutting White Shadow\",\"Silverwind Nargacuga\",\"Silverwind\",\"White Gale\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Silverwind Nargacuga\",\"content\":\"Silverwind Nargacuga shares a resemblance with the common Nargacuga but has white fur, bright striped patterns, and extra tail spikes that are always extended. They are typically larger than regular Nargacugas.\\n\\nSilverwind Nargacugas are faster, stronger, and more adept at using their tail spines than regular Nargacugas. They can create powerful shockwaves with swift tail swings, capable of cutting through defenses and causing deep gashes that lead to bleeding.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Bleeding\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 1617 cm - 2127 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":99,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":99,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":101,\"keys\":[\"Swift Wyvern\",\"Blinking Nargacuga\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Blinking Nargacuga\",\"content\":\"Blinking Nargacuga has shiny white scales, bright white fur, and a bright red underside. Its wings, tail spikes, and talons are also red, and its beak is gold. When enraged, it leaves behind red eye trails and its tail spikes are constantly splayed out, with a red tint to its afterimages.\\n\\nBlinking Nargacuga is similar to regular Nargacuga in movement but with enhanced attacks. Its teleportation and spike-shooting moves are more powerful, and it can create blades of wind that pull in hunters before shredding them.\\n\\nBlinking Nargacuga is extremely aggressive, fighting with swift ferocity and delivering quick successive attacks to overwhelm hunters. It punishes those who fail to evade specific moves, such as the \\\"Vacuum Slash.\\\"\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 1617 cm - 2127 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":100,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":100,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":102,\"keys\":[\"Flurry of Frosted Fangs\",\"Barioth\",\"Ice Tusk Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Barioth\",\"content\":\"Barioth (Also Called: \\\"Ice Tusk Wyvern\\\", \\\"Flurry of Frosted Fangs\\\") is a quadrupedal Flying Wyvern with icy white plates, saber-toothed cat features, and formidable orange tusks. Its forelegs are longer and stronger, adorned with deadly wing spikes, while its forked tail is ridged with orange spikes.\\n\\nBarioth is an aggressive and territorial Flying Wyvern with exceptional speed and agility. It uses its fangs, claws, and wings to slide on ice, making it challenging for hunters. Barioth can wield its tail as a club, causing Iceblight. It performs homing glide attacks and creates tornadoes with its wind blast. In a rage, its eyes turn red, signaling increased aggression. When fatigued, it feeds on Popo or Anteka.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1888 cm - 2580 cm / Height: Medium\\nFlying Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayI