"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":118,\"keys\":[\"Nocturnal Bird\",\"Malfestio\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Malfestio\",\"content\":\"Malfestio (Also called: \\\"Nocturnal Bird\\\"), resembling an owl, has blue plumage, a grayish belly, yellow collar, and a white face with a small beak and red eyes. It features long tufts on its head, yellow hints on its legs, and scaly feet with two talons. Its wings have bright blue membranes with blade-like claws, and its flattened tail ends in a three-pointed shape. Like a real owl, it can turn its head around to see behind itself.\\n\\nMalfestio utilizes its feathers to produce yellow scales, disorienting prey and inducing confusion. It can emit an ultrasound beam to easily put prey to sleep. The hidden claws along its wings are revealed in rage mode, serving as weapons during this heightened state.\\n\\nMalfestio is a nocturnal predator that uses its talons and wing claws to attack prey. Like Nargacuga, it sleeps in trees to avoid terrestrial predators.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep, Confusion\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Water Element\\nLength: 305 cm - 758 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":117,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":117,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":119,\"keys\":[\"Hidden Haze\",\"Nightcloak Malfestio\",\"Nightcloak\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nightcloak Malfestio\",\"content\":\"Nightcloak Malfestio has golden scales on its chest and the edges of its wings and bright red wing webbing and tail feathers. Its tail feathers are dark purple in color and resemble a four-pointed claw.\\n\\nIn addition to using larger clouds of confusion scales, Nightcloak Malfestio have the ability to turn invisible, like Lucent Nargacuga or Chameleos. They can also steal items from hunters.\\n\\nNightcloak Malfestio's use of invisibility allows it to more easily sneak up on prey, giving it a more aggressive disposition. Its devilish behavior and abilities mean that hunters require special permission to hunt it.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep, Confusion\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 353 cm - 858 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":118,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":118,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":120,\"keys\":[\"Qurupeco\",\"Colorful Bird\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Qurupeco\",\"content\":\"The Qurupeco, a large bird with Pterosaur-like features, has a lime green body, iridescent purple feathers, and a short brown crest. Its red vocal sac inflates when calling, and it has bulky wing growths that create sparks for fiery explosions. The tail unfolds as a warning. The feet, partially webbed with three frontal digits, complete its distinct appearance.\\n\\nThe Qurupeco (Also called: \\\"Colorful Bird\\\") posesses a masterful vocal mimicry that summons aid, heals, and boosts other monsters. Delicate with a soft crest, breaking its beak and wingtips yields extra rewards. Inflated vocal sac makes it susceptible to loud noises; Sonic Bombs or explosions interrupt its abilities. Capable of flight, it moves around, preventing traps while fleeing.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Defense Down, Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 772 cm - 1085 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":119,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":119,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":121,\"keys\":[\"Crimson Qurupeco\",\"Crimson Colorful Bird\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Crimson Qurupeco\",\"content\":\"Unlike the normal variety, this subspecies is red and blue in color. The electric flints are unique to this subspecies.\\n\\nThis Qurupeco subspecies creates electric shocks with wing talons and conductive mucus, causing Thunderblight instead of fire explosions. It can produce a blinding flash and requires Earplugs Skill to block its roar. The vocal sac appears during performances, allowing it to heal or boost monsters. If interrupted, the heal or boost applies to hunters. It can make summoned monsters enter Rage mode instantly with a new song ability.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Defense Down, Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 347 cm - 1085 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":120,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":120,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":122,\"keys\":[\"Poison Bewitching Bird\",\"Pukei-Pukei\",\"Gluttonous Gullet\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Pukei-Pukei\",\"content\":\"Pukei-Pukei (Also called: \\\"Poison Bewitching Bird\\\", \\\"Gluttonous Gullet\\\"), resembling a chameleon with color-shifting ability, has frog-like eyes, wings, and green feather-like scales. Vibrant feathers adorn its neck and wings, while the underbelly is covered in white osteoderm-like platings.\\n\\nPukei-Pukei stores food properties in its mouth and tail, blending them with poison for different effects. For instance, eating a Scatternut gives its poison a stunning ability.\\n\\nObservations show Pukei-Pukei bullies weaker monsters but retreats from stronger foes. It often flees at the first sign of danger. Enraged Pukei-Pukei exhibits red head and wing feathers, while fatigue fades the color and narrows its eyes.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Stun\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 970 cm - 1344 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":121,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":121,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":123,\"keys\":[\"Coral Pukei-Pukei\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Coral Pukei-Pukei\",\"content\":\"Coral Pukei-Pukei (Also called: \\\"Water Bewitching Bird\\\"), a variant of the species, has bright orange coloring on its face, feet, and front wing claws that turn red when enraged. The body is pinkish-red, and the underbelly and tail tip are violet.\\n\\nCoral Pukei-Pukei, distinct from the regular species, employs water as its primary element of attack. It stores water in its tail by consuming sponge-like plants in the Coral Highlands, enabling it to shoot high-pressure water beams. It can also release water balls and perform aggressive attacks, using its tail more effectively compared to the standard Pukei-Pukei.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 970 cm - 1344 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":122,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":122,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":124,\"keys\":[\"Feathered Frenzy\",\"Aknosom\",\"Parasol Bird\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Bird Wyvern\",\"Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"Medium Monster\"],\"comment\":\"Aknosom\",\"content\":\"Aknosom (Also called: \\\" Parasol Bird\\\", \\\"Feathered Frenzy\\\"), crane-like, has a red and gold parasol-like collar, extending to wings and an eye-like head crest for intimidation. It sports a long beak, yellow eyes, and white scales, some feathered. With long legs and a hook-like tail, Aknosom can stand on one leg.\\n\\nAknosom, territorial, displays its crest to intimidate intruders. It uses its collar defensively as a shield or bludgeoning weapon, and its tough beak can be thrust into the ground. Aknosom spits small fireballs, rushes at high speed, and employs blade-tipped wings for swiping attacks. It is also capable of flight and aerial maneuvers.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 763 cm - 1043 cm / Height: ~ tank size\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":123,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":123,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":125,\"keys\":[\"Gargwa\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gargwa\",\"content\":\"Gargwa, with likely vestigial wings, are normally docile herbivores but turn aggressive and flee when threatened. In their escape, they often leave behind an egg or guano. Coexisting with Yukumo village as livestock, Gargwa have been known to attack hunters occasionally.\\n\\nSize: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":124,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":124,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":126,\"keys\":[\"Velociprey\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Velociprey\",\"content\":\"Velociprey resemble dromaeosaurid dinosaurs. These monsters have blue scales with black stripes, a red crest, yellow eyes, and a white belly. They travel in packs and inhabit diverse environments.\\n\\nExperienced hunters manage Velociprey packs well, but their swift movements and leaping abilities pose challenges for the unfamiliar, especially when carrying items like eggs and ores.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: None\\nLength: ~ 635 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":125,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":125,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":127,\"keys\":[\"Velocidrome\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Bird Wyvern\",\"Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"Small Monster\",\"Velociprey\"],\"comment\":\"Velocidrome\",\"content\":\"The large, bright red crest over its blue hide signifies to other Velociprey that it is fit to be their leader.\\n\\nDue to its usual weak physical strength, Velocidrome are forced to group up into packs whilst hunting.\\n\\nVelocidrome leads Velociprey packs, sometimes with two leaders to enhance hunting strength and split into two groups for more effective hunting.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 590 cm - 1736 cm / Height: ~ human size\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":126,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":126,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":128,\"keys\":[\"Giaprey\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Giaprey\",\"content\":\"They have crystal blue scales with sky blue stripes. Although they are of a different species, White Velociprey have been seen in packs of Velociprey. Like all of the '-prey' family, this sub-species also fights in a pack.\\n\\nThey are a little stronger, physically and defensively, than the average Velociprey, and are noticeably tougher than their counterparts in battle.\\n\\nThey also gained the ability to spit ice to attack hunters in second generation games, being able to freeze enemies like Blangonga. Although stronger than Velociprey, they're hardly any more dangerous.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 577 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":127,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":127,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":129,\"keys\":[\"Giadrome\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Giadrome\",\"content\":\"It is physically very similar to the Velocidrome, the only key difference being the pale blue colouration and the presence of a frost sac.\\n\\nNot only does it sport more powerful attack power and higher defense than ordinary Giaprey, it is also capable of spitting a frozen substance that can immobilize prey and foes alike.\\n\\nThe Giadrome is quite territorial towards other monsters and other Giadromes. It travels alongside its pack and coordinates attacks using barks and calls.\\n\\nElement: Ice\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 649 cm - 1048 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":128,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":128,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":130,\"keys\":[\"Genprey\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Genprey\",\"content\":\"Their bodies are covered in a colorful yellow and green hide, with a pair of yellow crests over their eyes.\\n\\nGenprey are capable of inflicting paralysis with their fangs, and like other theropod Bird Wyverns, can leap great distances at foes.\\n\\nGenprey operate under the rule of their pack leader, the Gendrome. They will respond aggressively to intruders, and will rally to the Gendrome's call to gang up on a larger foe.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 635 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":129,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":129,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":131,\"keys\":[\"Gendrome\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gendrome\",\"content\":\"Their bodies are covered in a colorful yellow and green hide, with a pair of yellow crests over their eyes. Hunters can easily identify a Gendrome by their big crest and slightly larger size compared to a Genprey. The crest signifies leadership over the pack.\\n\\nWith a pack to protect them and paralyzing fangs, they are a force to be reckoned with. Considerably harder than a Velocidrome, Gendrome pose a challenge to novice hunters. Quick attacks and high speed allow them to attack with surprising power.\\n\\nGendrome are in charge of making sure their pack is kept alive and healthy. They choose which prey to hunt, and will often lead the attack. Gendrome will also actively patrol their territory alongside a handful of Genprey.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis, Stun\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 615 cm - 1037 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":130,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":130,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":132,\"keys\":[\"Ioprey\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ioprey\",\"content\":\"Ioprey have lithe, raptor-esque bodies. They have vivid red skin, with some black markings and purplish lavender colouration by the limbs. Ioprey have very distinctive head crests, large and well rounded. Their lower jaw curls outwards significantly.\\n\\nIoprey are easily distinguishable from other Raptor species due to their larger size and bulbous frog-like throat sac. This enlarged throat houses the Ioprey's potent poison sac, which gives it the ability to spit toxins at its foes.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 639 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":131,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":131,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":133,\"keys\":[\"Iodrome\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Iodrome\",\"content\":\"It is significantly larger than normal Ioprey and possesses a larger crest. Unlike other pack leaders, Iodrome has a more amphibian look, with salamander-like skin that seems to glisten with moisture, and a frog-like throat sac. It also lacks the sharp claws of its relatives, relying more on poison to bring down prey like Aptonoth and enemies.\\n\\nIodrome is a threat due to its speed, agility, considerable strength and poison. When threatened, Iodrome spits Poison from the poison sac in its throat.\\n\\nIodrome is the leader of a pack of Ioprey, and always travels with its pack for protection.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 619 cm - 1641 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":132,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":132,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":134,\"keys\":[\"Jaggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Jaggi\",\"content\":\"In this stage, Jaggi are mostly pink with purple details, cream-colored underbellies, barbed tails, and sizable frills for intimidation or appearing larger to other monsters.\\n\\nJaggi and their kind, while more cooperative than other Raptors, are easily dealt with, especially by novice hunters. Their boisterous nature includes vocalizing warnings, dividing their focus between intimidation and attacking intruders.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nHeight: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":133,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":133,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":135,\"keys\":[\"Jaggia\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Jaggia\",\"content\":\"Jaggia, the female Jaggi, are larger and bulkier than immature males, with a blue-purple hue, orange areas on limbs and necks, and cream-colored underbellies. Their tails lack barbs, featuring soft, feather-like accents, and their frills are more subdued, hanging limply.\\n\\nJaggia generally live near the nest and are responsible for defending it and raising young. Smaller than mature males, but larger and tougher than the pack's countless young males. They also operate under orders from the alpha.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nHeight: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":134,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":134,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":136,\"keys\":[\"Great Jaggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Jaggi\",\"content\":\"Great Jaggi's distinctive features include its frill, lavender scales with crimson and tangerine overrides on the frills and abdomen, and fur along the neck and back to the middle of the tail. Its muzzle is thinner and more wrinkled than other Bird Wyverns. The tail has blunt barbs on each side, used in tail whip attacks.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 822 cm - 1261 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":135,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":135,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":137,\"keys\":[\"Baggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Baggi\",\"content\":\"Baggi resemble small theropod dinosaurs called dromaeosaurs. Their hide is primarily blue, with a grayish underbelly and a streak of yellow between. Patches of black fur can be found on the back of the head, above the shoulders, and especially the tail.\\n\\nBaggi have the ability to put other creatures to sleep via a tranquilizing fluid, which only lasts for a few seconds. Baggi have the same attacks as their Jaggi cousins, but attack more without delay. They will spend less time hissing and will rush at hunters without warning.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: ~ 365 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":136,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":136,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":138,\"keys\":[\"Great Baggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Baggi\",\"content\":\"ts eyes will glow yellow in the dark. Great Baggi are matured male Baggi that have taken over a pack of their own. Great Baggi is also slightly larger than the Great Jaggi.\\n\\nLocated on its head is a crest that can be obtained in a way similar to Great Jaggi's frill.\\n\\nIt has developed its own unique ability; it can spit a tranquilizing liquid that inflicts sleep on its prey or hunters. It also has developed the ability to command Baggi to surround prey or hunters and spit tranquilizing liquid at them with a roar.\\n\\nGreat Baggi and Great Jaggi are often seen to be hostile towards other boss monsters; when in the same area they will occasionally cease fighting the hunter to attack other monsters.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 839 cm - 1457 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":137,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":137,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":139,\"keys\":[\"Wroggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Wroggi\",\"content\":\"Wroggi are similar in body structure to Jaggi and Baggi, and are covered in a slick, water-resistant hide of an orange colouration. They have a pair of poison sacs on either side of their heads.\\n\\nWroggi have poison sacs that they use to weaken enemies. Their movements and body structure are similar to that of Jaggia. Wroggi are poisonous, but are not as strong or as resistant to poison as their leader.\\n\\nWroggi live along with their Alpha leader, Great Wroggi.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: ~ 365 cm / Height: Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":138,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":138,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":140,\"keys\":[\"Great Wroggi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Wroggi\",\"content\":\"The Great Wroggi has a slick salamander-like skin similar to the Iodrome, and, like its close relatives the Great Jaggi and Great Baggi, Great Wroggi are usually accompanied by a group of their smaller kin - in this case, Wroggi.\\n\\nThe most prominent feature of a Great Wroggi is its delicate, translucent sac-like organ around the neck. Because of its translucence, poison can be seen in the sac before it spews out as a toxic mist.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 831 cm - 1168 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":139,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":139,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":141,\"keys\":[\"Maccao\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Maccao\",\"content\":\"Maccao has a body shape similar to the dromaeosaurid dinosaurs. Its body is covered in green feathers with red underbelly. The legs and hands are covered in hard brown shells, which can also be found on its thick tail.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: ~ 323 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":140,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":140,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":142,\"keys\":[\"Great Maccao\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Maccao\",\"content\":\"The Great Maccao's feathered crest sets them apart from its Maccao pack. Although superficially similar to its younger brethren, a Great Maccao is bigger and bulkier, with more brightly-colored plumage. It also has powerful legs it uses to kick threats and to move with great speed, and its spiked tail allows it to propel itself forward and jump with tremendous force.\\n\\nGreat Maccao has powerful legs it uses to kick threats and to move with great speed. It can stand on its tail and launch itself forward. Should its tail be damaged, it will be heavily restricted due to relying on its tail for offense and movement.\\n\\nUnlike other Theropod Bird Wyverns, Great Maccao exhibits little to no control over its pack. It would much rather run than stay and fight alongside the Maccao. However, it is known to work with its pack to hunt large prey.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 701 cm - 1274 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":141,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":141,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":143,\"keys\":[\"Izuchi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Izuchi\",\"content\":\"Izuchi resembles a generic dromaeosaur. It has a brownish red coat with pale yellow lines across the body and white patches of fur on its head, back and tail, the latter of which ends in a sickle-like blade.\\n\\nIzuchi uses its tail as a means of attacking and climbing trees, usually for fruit. Izuchi is an omnivore that feeds on a variety of food. Most Izuchis can be found in herds lead by Great Izuchi, usually in two males. The two males are the best fighters that assist Great Izuchi in hunting for prey and defending territory. Should one Izuchi fall, another will be called over by Great Izuchi to aid it. Izuchi are aggressive monsters that will attack intruders and loyal to their pack.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Water Element\\nLength: ~ 390 cm / Height: ~Small\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":142,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":142,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":144,\"keys\":[\"Trinity of Terror\",\"Great Izuchi\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Izuchi\",\"content\":\"Great Izuchi has short orange fur with white patches on the head, neck, back, and tail. Cream-colored scales beneath turn dark indigo toward the arms and legs. It has a long snout with cobra-like fangs, orange eyes, and large gray underbelly plating. The arms have three digits, with a hook-like middle finger. The tail features a bony, sharp scythe-like blade for attacking.\\n\\nThe Great Izuchi (Also called: \\\"Trinity of Terror\\\"), a cooperative Bird Wyvern, leads a pack of at least three with remarkable intelligence. It commands sharp companions in combination attacks using their scythe-like tails. Agile and capable of regurgitating rocks, it surpasses the smaller Izuchi in spitting range.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 946 cm - 1343 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":143,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":143,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":145,\"keys\":[\"Bird Brain\",\"Scratching Bird\",\"Kulu\",\"Kulu-Ya-Ku\",\"Ovivore Outlaw\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kulu-Ya-Ku\",\"content\":\"Kulu-Ya-Ku (Also called: \\\"Kulu\\\" for short, \\\"Scratching Bird\\\", \\\"Ovivore Outlaw\\\", or mockingly called: \\\"Bird Brain\\\") a raptorial Bird Wyvern, has a body shape similar to Velocidrome, with light brown scales, feathers on the head and arms, and a Dodo-like face. Its tongue has four spikes to prevent egg yolk spillage.\\n\\nKulu-Ya-Ku uses small boulders for defense and offense, throwing them or using a jumping slam for stun. It steals eggs, and hunters can dislodge rocks with Slinger Ammos or weapon strikes. In Master Rank, it uses ore chunks or flint rocks, with ore causing more damage and stun, and flint rocks possibly causing combustion. The factors influencing rock choice are unknown. The head and arms of Kulu-Ya-Ku can be wounded.\\n\\nUnlike other raptorial bird wyverns, Kulu-Ya-Ku are very docile and calm when coming into contact with hunters. If attacked, however, they will fight back.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Stun\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 902 cm - 1126 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":144,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":144,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":146,\"keys\":[\"Tzitzi-Ya-Ku\",\"Dazzling Bird\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tzitzi-Ya-Ku\",\"content\":\"Tzitzi-Ya-Ku, a medium-sized navy blue Bird Wyvern, features powerful back legs, muscular forelegs with three grasping claws, and retractable, brightly colored frills on each side of its head. Short spines line its back, and it has wide sturdy feet.\\n\\nTzitzi-Ya-Ku emits bright flashes from its head fins, disorienting attackers and prey. Its powerful hind legs deliver potent kicks in battle. In Master Rank, it can change direction while preparing the flash. Wounding its head disables the flash. This low-ranking monster uses its dark coloration to blend into the Coral Highlands' shadows, stalking prey. When threatened, it stuns stronger monsters with flashes and escapes. Tzitzi-Ya-Ku interrupts battles by flashing monsters in the area, annoying both hunters and creatures.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Stun\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 786 cm - 1117 cm / Height: Medium\\nBird Wyvern, Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":145,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":145,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":147,\"keys\":[\"Bird Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Bird Wyvern\",\"content\":\"They are a small to medium sized class that includes Flying Wyverns with slender bodies that are bipedal and, in some cases, either have wings or lack wings.\\n\\nThere are two distinct types of Bird Wyverns: Flying Bird Wyverns and Theropod Bird Wyverns.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":146,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":146,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":148,\"keys\":[\"Flying Bird Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Flying Bird Wyvern\",\"content\":\"Flying Bird Wyverns exhibit similar characteristics to True Wyverns, with a bipedal stance along with developed and functional wings. Many of these possess a hard, sharp beak which can be used to peck at attackers, and generally behave in a bird-like manner.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":147,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":147,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":149,\"keys\":[\"Theropod Bird Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Theropod Bird Wyverns\",\"content\":\"Theropod Bird Wyverns are reminiscent of Brute Wyverns: flightless, bipedal creatures with long tails and powerful legs. Unlike Brute Wyverns however, these monsters are generally quite small. Furthermore, Theropod Bird Wyverns almost always live under a social hierarchy, with young individuals, females and beta males led by a strong, dominant alpha male, which can command and control his subjects during combat.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":148,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":148,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":150,\"keys\":[\"Terrifying Violent Wyvern\",\"Deviljho\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Deviljho\",\"content\":\"Deviljho (Also called: \\\"Terrifying Violent Wyvern\\\") is a large, forest green Brute Wyvern with a muscular upper body. Its hide has short, jagged spines along the back and tail. Deviljho has a narrow snout with a large lower jaw, featuring multiple rows of teeth. Its hind legs are massive, while the forelegs are tiny and poorly developed. When enraged, its back and shoulder muscles swell, revealing scars, and some skin areas turn bright red.\\n\\nDeviljho has powerful jaws for bone-crushing bites and tossing prey, as well as throwing rocks. Its strong hind legs allow high-speed running and leaping. When enraged, it emits a deadly Dragon Element cloud from its mouth.\\n\\nDeviljho, a nomadic super-predator, roams extensively to claim territory from other monsters. With a high energy demand, it is cannibalistic and consumes prey alive for quick energy replenishment.\\n\\nElement: Dragon\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Defence Down\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1803 cm - 4097 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":149,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":149,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":151,\"keys\":[\"Savage Deviljho\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Savage Deviljho\",\"content\":\"In its enraged state, Savage Deviljho exhibits a dark red Dragon Element haze around its face. The eyes turn blood-red, and its skin changes to a light brownish color. Scales are slightly darker than normal, and tailfangs are blood-red.\\n\\nSavage Deviljho is faster, stronger, and more tenacious than the average Deviljho. It exhibits larger breath attacks, complex use of the Dragon Element in both rage and non-rage states, and additional voracious attack patterns.\\n\\nElement: Dragon\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Defence Down\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1803 cm - 4097 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":150,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":150,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":152,\"keys\":[\"Fierce Jaw Wyvern\",\"Relentless Ruffian\",\"Anjanath\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Anjanath\",\"content\":\"Anjanath (Also called: \\\"Fierce Jaw Wyvern\\\", \\\"Relentless Ruffian\\\"), resembling a Tyrannosaurus, has pink skin, grey fur on its back, and a dark pelt covering its back. Large fangs protrude from its lower jaw, and it has a bulky tail with quills. Despite its powerful hind legs, its forearms are small. Anjanath can flare out dorsal sails and unfold a nasal crest, using its flame sac to produce a fiery glow when agitated.\\n\\nAnjanath, a formidable predator, can lift and throw large creatures, breathe fire, and becomes relentless when provoked. In rage, it reveals nostrils, breathes heavily, and flashes fins to threaten. Hunters can wound its head, legs, and sever its tail.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1448 cm - 2008 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":151,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":151,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":153,\"keys\":[\"Fulgur Anjanath\",\"Thunder Jaw Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Fulgur Anjanath\",\"content\":\"Fulgur Anjanath, a variant of the standard species, displays a distinct appearance with bright white fur, light grey hide, orange head, and dark grey stripes. When charged, it exhibits blue crackles of electricity on its flared dorsal fins and has a bright blue glow on its nasal crest and inside its mouth.\\n\\nFulgur Anjanath (Also called: \\\"Thunder Jaw Wyvern\\\"), akin to its standard form, utilizes formidable jaws and legs for offense. Its unique trait is an affinity for Thunder Element, enhancing its physical strength. When charged, it electrifies mucus for ranged attacks, enabling it to contend with formidable predators.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 1481 cm - 2008 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":152,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":152,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":154,\"keys\":[\"Burst Hammer Wyvern\",\"Uragaan\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Uragaan\",\"content\":\"Uragaan boasts a gold-colored hide adorned with hard crystals on its back and a rock-like shell on its chin. In volcanic regions, it attaches explosive rocks to its tar-covered underbelly for additional offensive capabilities.\\n\\nUragaan (Also called: \\\"Burst Hammer Wyvern\\\") showcases its signature ability by rolling into a wheel, increasing speed and agility to crush hunters. It can emit sleep gas or flames, inducing sleep or Fireblight, depending on the color. Uragaan attacks with a large jaw slam and a wide tail sweep, flinging explosive rocks that can later explode during a heavy jaw smash.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Sleep\\nWeakness: Water Element, Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 410 cm - 3344 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":153,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":153,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":155,\"keys\":[\"Crystalbeard Uragaan\",\"Treasure Clad\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Crystalbeard Uragaan\",\"content\":\"Crystalbeard Uragaan (Also called: \\\"Treasure Clad\\\") shares the same body shape as regular Uragaan but features an orange-red coloration with shiny blue-purple minerals protruding from its tail and chin.\\n\\nCrystalbeard Uragaan retains Uragaan's movesets with minor changes. It occasionally releases sleep gas by throwing crystal-like rocks from its tail and can fling rocks at enemies using its chin, similar to Deviljho.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Sleep, Stun\\nWeakness: Water Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 2548 cm - 2920 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":154,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":154,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":156,\"keys\":[\"Steel Uragaan\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Steel Uragaan\",\"content\":\"Steel Uragaan appears to have a hide of a deep metallic blue, rather than the golden hide of the common species. It is speculated that this altered coloration is due to the monster feeding on different types of ores.\\n\\nSteel Uragaan can cause the Soiled status with sulfuric gas and burning rocks. The rocks release soiling gas when exploded.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Souled, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Water Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 2548 cm - 2920 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":155,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":155,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":157,\"keys\":[\"Radobaan\",\"Bone Hammer Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Radobaan\",\"content\":\"Radobaan (Also called: \\\"Bone Hammer Wyvern\\\") resembles Uragaan but distinguishes itself with bone armor, including a spiny vertebrae row and Diablos horns. This bone armor can be dislodged with sufficient damage.\\n\\nRadobaan, like Uragaan, can roll into a wheel shape for both movement and attacks, dispersing a sleeping agent, causing tremors, and hurling bones as projectiles. While more agile, its smaller stature makes it easier to knock off balance when rolling. It can regain its bone armor by digging through piles of bones in the Rotten Vale, even after it has been broken off.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Sleep\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 1587 cm - 2182 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":156,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":156,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":158,\"keys\":[\"Duramboros\",\"Tail Hammer Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Duramboros\",\"content\":\"Duramboros (Also called: \\\"Tail Hammer Wyvern\\\") is a bulky, bovine monster with a thick outer hide, armored plates along its back, a massive tail club, twin brow horns, and energy-rich dorsal humps. Its slow lifestyle allows moss and algae to grow on its hide.\\n\\nDuramboros, a herbivore, feeds on fallen trees using its horns and tail club. Generally docile, it can become aggressive if provoked, utilizing its tail club, horns, and mass for attacks. It displays a unique behavior of twirling to build momentum and hurl itself at attackers.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Stun\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Poison Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 1317 cm - 2611 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":157,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":157,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":159,\"keys\":[\"Axe Tail Wyvern\",\"Duramboros\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rust Duramboros\",\"content\":\"Rust Duramboros (Also called: \\\"Axe Tail Wyvern\\\"), residing in a sandy environment, has a copper-pink tone on its brown hide. It shares similarities with ordinary Duramboros but features a wider, axe-like tail club instead of a spherical one. The lack of moss and algae exposure maintains a more juvenile appearance even in adulthood.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Muddy\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 2116 cm - 4454 cm / Height: Large\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":158,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":158,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":160,\"keys\":[\"Ferocious Bull Wyvern\",\"Banbaro\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Banbaro\",\"content\":\"Banbaro (Also called: \\\"Ferocious Bull Wyvern\\\") is a large and heavy-set Brute Wyvern. Most of its body is covered in stout white fur, with portions on its head, legs, and arms being covered in gray scales. Its giant horns are its defining characteristic. These stout, pinkish horns end in broad, moose-like antlers. When enraged, a small horn-like projection on its snout folds out.\\n\\nBanbaro is normally calm but turns aggressive when provoked. In battle, it charges, digs up soil for a debris blast, throws trees as projectiles, and leaves lava trails with volcanic rock. Its tail sweeps away debris piles.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 2164 cm - 2957 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":159,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":159,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":161,\"keys\":[\"Gastodon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gastodon\",\"content\":\"Gastodon resemble a cross between a theropod dinosaur and a bison. They are covered in scales but have large furry manes and horns reminiscent of a bison. When angered, they will glow red.\\n\\nGastodons, found in the Elder's Recess, are aggressive and attack hunters on sight. They form herds and also engage larger monsters. Despite their aggression, they are preyed upon by various predators in the area.\\n\\nBrute Wyvern, Small Monster\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":160,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":160,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":162,\"keys\":[\"Kestodon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kestodon\",\"content\":\"Kestodon heavily resemble the Pachycephalosaurus, a dinosaur famous for its unique-looking skull. Male Kestodon are bright orange in color and have a large head crest for headbutting rivals, whereas females are bronze in color and lack the head crest found in males.\\n\\nKestodon are an aggressive species that will turn hostile once spotted. Females will alert the pack of danger, while the males will violently charge would-be threats. They immediately become hostile when approached closely, but will not attack other monsters.\\n\\nBrute Wyvern, Small Monster\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":161,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":161,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":163,\"keys\":[\"Glavenus\",\"Cutting Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Glavenus\",\"content\":\"Glavenus (Also called: \\\"Cutting Wyvern\\\"), a formidable Brute Wyvern, has dark red scales with blue bony plates along its back. It boasts a unique sword-like tail that changes color during battles. Its hind legs are muscular, while the smaller arms are less effective in combat. The face, with sturdy plating, resembles a Carnotaurus, while the overall proportions are akin to a Tyrannosaurus.\\n\\nAggressive and intelligent, Glavenus uses its sword-like tail skillfully. It sharpens the tail in its mouth, heating it up for more powerful attacks. Swallowing soot and ore, it creates a magma-like substance in its throat, which it spits out to cause explosive attacks. The heated tail gradually cools down, prompting Glavenus to resharpen it for optimal performance.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Bleeding\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 2234 cm - 3174 cm / Height: ~ small house size\\nBrute Wyvern \",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":162,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":162,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":164,\"keys\":[\"Sulfuric Cutting Wyvern\",\"Acidic Glavenus\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Acidic Glavenus\",\"content\":\"Acidic Glavenus' body is a variety of emerald and blue shades, with dark grey spikes and horns. His tail is usually covered in yellow crystals, which, when scraped off reveal a dull blue, katana-like blade. His eyes are dark red.\\n\\nAcidic Glavenus has enhanced control over its tail attacks with a lighter tail, executing precise slashes and jabs. When covered in acidic crystals, it behaves more like the standard Glavenus, and its corrosive tail can induce Defense Down on contact.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Defense Down\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 2234 cm - 3174 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":163,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":163,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":165,\"keys\":[\"Hellblade\",\"Black Knight of Ferocious Flames\",\"Incinerating Blade\",\"Hellblade Glavenus\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Hellblade Glavenus\",\"content\":\"Hellblade Glavenus (Also called: \\\"Hellblade\\\", \\\"Black Knight of Ferocious Flames\\\", \\\"Incinerating Blade\\\") resemble a large, enraged Glavenus. In comparison, they have a deep red coloration; their horns and dorsal spines are larger, and blood red in color, and their throat-situated flame sacs and bladelike tails either glow with heat or have a magma-like texture.\\n\\nHellblade Glavenus produce a highly explosive powder that they can use to enhance their explosive spit, coat their tails, or emit with some attacks.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 2727 cm - 3409 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":164,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":164,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":166,\"keys\":[\"Landslide Wyvern\",\"Wasteland Warrior\",\"Barroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Barroth\",\"content\":\"Barroth (Also called: \\\"Landslide Wyvern\\\", \\\"Wasteland Warrior\\\"), a Brute Wyvern, features a distinctive crown on its skull with nostrils, rigid plates for protection, and a mouth filled with long, peg-shaped teeth.\\n\\nBarroth utilizes its heavy head to plow through the environment, causing damage and can submerge itself in mud to stay cool during hot desert days.\\n\\nBarroth, typically docile, becomes highly territorial when disturbed. It cools off by rolling in mud and will attack relentlessly if provoked, issuing a warning roar first. Additionally, it preys on Altaroth by attacking their nests.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Muddy, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1217 cm - 1744 cm / Height: Medium\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":165,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":165,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":167,\"keys\":[\"Ice Crushing Wyvern\",\"Jade Barroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Brute Wyvern\",\"Medium Monster\",\"Barroth\"],\"comment\":\"Jade Barroth\",\"content\":\"Jade Barroth, (Also called: \\\"Ice Crushing Wyvern\\\"), use snow for protection, similar to how Barroth use mud. They sport a larger crown compared to their desert counterpart and their hide as a beautiful, jade colouring with greyish black legs and a yellow chest and stomach.\\n\\nJade Barroth are somewhat temperamental creatures that prefer a wide berth and can be docile if not provoked. But if angered, these creatures can be living nightmares, as they will relentlessly charge, bite, tail whip, and stomp their targets until they are dead.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1266 cm - 1744 cm / Height: Medium\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":166,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":166,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":168,\"keys\":[\"Brachydios\",\"Crushing Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Brachydios\",\"content\":\"Brachydios is recognized by its glowing, green slime-covered horn and \\\"fists,\\\" with an armored hide featuring plates and ridges made of obsidian. It boasts long, developed forelimbs, its primary means of defense. Though it has forelimb claws, they serve no apparent purpose in battle.\\n\\nBrachydios' forelimbs and horn are covered in a green slime mold with explosive properties. By slamming the ground or prey, it deposits the slime, which undergoes a powerful chemical reaction and explodes. The slime gradually depletes, but Brachydios can replenish it by priming with saliva. The substance is sticky; if it hits a hunter, it adheres and explodes. Brachydios is agile, using its hind legs and powerful attacks. Its durable shell withstands explosions and external attacks. When enraged, parts like fists and horn glow, causing instant explosions on impact.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Blastblight, Blastscourge, Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 1339 cm - 1932 cm / Height: Medium\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":167,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":167,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":169,\"keys\":[\"Raging Brachydios\",\"Crushing Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Raging Brachydios\",\"content\":\"Raging Brachydios sports a green shell with yellow-orange slime mold on its forelimbs, head, back, and tail that turns red when it becomes enraged. It is noticeably larger than normal Brachydios and moves slower as a result.\\n\\nRaging Brachydios, compared to the standard species, is physically tougher with a harder carapace and a more volatile explosive slime mold. The mold detonates faster and produces a stronger blast. Red slime turns even more volatile, exploding almost instantly. In a heightened state of rage, it loses most slime, adopting a cracked, scorched appearance with constant smoke. It replaces the explosive slime with molten, lava-like substance, burning anything in contact and causing widespread detonations. However, the damaged shell makes it more vulnerable, causing self-inflicted damage.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Slimeblight, Blastblight, Blastscourge, Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 2130 cm - 2282 cm / Height: Large\\nBrute Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":168,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":168,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":170,\"keys\":[\"Brute Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Brute Wyvern\",\"content\":\"Brute Wyverns are a group of flightless wyverns, resembling nonfictional theropods. Adapted for land life, they rely on powerful hindlimbs for movement. Most possess small, barely functional forelimbs, though exceptions exist with heavily developed limbs for combat.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":169,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":169,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":171,\"keys\":[\"Zinogre\",\"Thunder Wolf Wyvern\",\"Spark of Blue\",\"Lord of Lightning\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Zinogre\",\"content\":\"Zinogre (Also called: \\\"Thunder Wolf Wyvern\\\", \\\"Spark of Blue\\\", \\\"Lord of Lightning\\\") is a quadrupedal monster with wolf-like features, powerful limbs, and sharp fangs. Despite its size, it is agile and can perform impressive aerial and land-based maneuvers. The spikes on its body lie flat but become erect when it builds up an electric charge.\\n\\nZinogre can charge itself by summoning Thunderbugs, enhancing its attacks and agility. The charge has two levels, with the second being more powerful. If Zinogre loses the charge, it becomes less aggressive until it can gather Thunderbugs again. The states of charge can be visually identified, with Thunderbugs flying around after the first charge and Zinogre's fur standing on end after the second. The charged state makes Zinogre vulnerable to stagger and cancellation by hunters.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1217 cm - 2144 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":170,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":170,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":172,\"keys\":[\"Hell Wolf Wyvern\",\"Stygian Zinogre\",\"Emperor of Hell\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Stygian Zinogre\",\"content\":\"Stygian Zinogre (Also called: \\\"Hell Wolf Wyvern\\\", \\\"Emperor of Hell\\\") sport color schemes of grey, white and red and are typically larger than normal individuals.\\n\\nStygian Zinogre's attacks have a distinctive crimson red/black lightning that inflicts Dragon Element damage. It absorbs bugs feeding on Dragonfell berries, resembling Great Thunderbugs. Released orbs from these bugs explode on contact, causing substantial damage to hunters.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Dracophage Erosion, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 1397 cm - 1887 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":171,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":171,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":173,\"keys\":[\"Golden Thunder Prince\",\"Thunderlord Zinogre\",\"True Awakening\",\"Thunder Wolf Wyvern King\",\"Thunderlord\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Thunderlord Zinogre\",\"content\":\"Thunderlord Zinogre (Also called: \\\"Thunderlord\\\", \\\"True Awakening\\\", \\\"Golden Thunder Prince\\\", \\\"Thunder Wolf Wyvern King\\\") resembles a fully-charged Zinogre, with one horn much larger than the other, green scales, and golden fur and claws. It crackles with green electricity, turning golden in its \\\"Ultracharged\\\" state.\\n\\nThunderlord Zinogre has the same moves as Zinogre, although they are improved dramatically. Thunderlord Zinogre also has new ones of its own. Unlike other Zinogre, Thunderlord Zinogre is already in supercharged state which they can freely go in Rage Mode and reach a new charged state called the \\\"Ultracharged\\\" state. Thunderlord Zinogre will use their horns to much greater effect than other Zinogre.\\n\\nThe Thunderlord Zinogre is a truly dangerous monster that is much stronger than a normal Zinogre. Hunters are required to have a special permit in order to hunt them.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1488 cm - 1918 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":172,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":172,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":174,\"keys\":[\"Apex Zinogre\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apex Zinogre\",\"content\":\"The Apex Zinogre has yellow fur, red eyes, dark greenish-blue scales, and small glowing red marks on the underbelly. Larger orange marks appear on the forelegs when charged up.\\n\\nThe Apex Zinogre exhibits new, aggressive attacks, including a forward flip followed by an electric claw slam, an electric uppercut releasing shockwaves, and a sequence involving creating and manipulating electric orbs, concluding with a howl as lightning rains down.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Fire Element, Water Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 1488 cm - 1918 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":173,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":173,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":175,\"keys\":[\"Jagras\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Jagras\",\"content\":\"Jagras are small, nimble creatures resembling wolves with light green scales, blue and reddish stripes, and a blue underbelly. Their body shape allows for quick movement and brief periods of standing upright.\\n\\nJagras are pack-oriented creatures that swiftly swarm potential prey, often led by the larger Great Jagras. They exhibit bold behavior but tend to flee to trees when faced with larger monsters. Interestingly, Jagras are drawn to raw meat dropped by hunters, and they will hide in trees if a significant threat is present. However, they may attack larger monsters that are knocked down.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nHeight: Small\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":174,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":174,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":176,\"keys\":[\"Thief Wyvern\",\"Punching Bag\",\"Great Glutton\",\"Great Jagras\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Jagras\",\"content\":\"Great Jagras (Also called: \\\"Thief Wyvern\\\", \\\"Great Glutton\\\" or mockingly called: \\\"Punching Bag\\\" since Great Jagras are often used for hunters to test their new weapons as there are too many Great Jagras) looks like an iguana with yellow scales, a bluish underside, and a dreadlock-like mane. Known for its massive stomach capacity, it swallows prey whole and regurgitates when damaged. The monster leaves slide trails and can be wounded on the head, front limbs, and belly.\\n\\nGreat Jagras swallows prey whole, using its weight as a weapon. It may vomit if its stomach is full, and its attacks vary based on its recent meals.\\n\\nGreat Jagras feeds on Aptonoth and Kestodon and regurgitates food for its pack. Deviljho may use Great Jagras as a living weapon.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 743 cm - 1997 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":175,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":175,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":177,\"keys\":[\"Girros\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Girros\",\"content\":\"Girros are snake-like Fanged Wyverns with a head and hood similar to a cobra. They have black onyx scales with yellow stripes on their neck. Girros also have red gill-like organs on the side of their neck.\\n\\nGirros, despite their size, are relentless attackers with paralyzing venom. In groups, they become extra aggressive and attack fallen or immobilized monsters.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nHeight: Small\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":176,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":176,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":178,\"keys\":[\"Paralyzing Thief Wyvern\",\"Great Girros\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Great Girros\",\"content\":\"Great Girros' head greatly resembles a cobra in appearance though it walks on all fours like a monitor lizard. It is covered in black onyx scales and has yellow stripes running down the back of its neck. On the side of its neck is a hood with red gill-like organs. The head and forelegs of the Great Girros can be wounded, and the tail can be severed.\\n\\nGreat Girros has large paralyzing fangs and can spit venom, causing paralysis. It can call other Girros for support during a fight, but damaging its hood disrupts this ability.\\n\\nGreat Girros (Also called: \\\"Paralyzing Thief Wyvern\\\") is an aggressive scavenger that feeds on corpses. It will attack other monsters, including Odogaron, but can be overpowered when Odogaron is freed from paralysis.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 937 cm - 1316 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":177,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":177,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":179,\"keys\":[\"Shamos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shamos\",\"content\":\"Shamos has a wolf-like body with orange eyes, red scales on its face, grayish-white body, navy-blue limbs, and a fish-like fin on its back.\\n\\nShamos have large eyes for night vision and hunt in packs. They are sensitive to light and retreat when exposed to it. They often group together to deter predators, particularly disliking Tzitzi-Ya-Ku's blinding flash.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nHeight: Small\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":178,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":178,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":180,\"keys\":[\"Dodogama\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Dodogama\",\"content\":\"Dodogama has a similar body type to its relative, Great Jagras, with blue scales and orange stripes covering its body. It has a massive bottom jaw used for storing rocks in its mouth, which will turn orange when they become volatile.\\n\\nDodogama defends itself by consuming rocks, turning them into explosive projectiles with its saliva. Damaging its jaw prematurely triggers rock explosions. Additionally, it can use a charging attack that inflicts Blast status.\\n\\nDeviljho can use Dodogama as a weapon, flailing it around. Despite being lower in the food chain, Dodogama defends itself with explosive projectiles. It generally fights only when provoked or when already engaged with another large monster.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Blastblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 977 cm - 2000 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":179,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":179,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":181,\"keys\":[\"Flying Thunder Wyvern\",\"Tobi Kadachi\",\"Flying Sparks\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tobi Kadachi\",\"content\":\"Tobi-Kadachi (Also called: \\\"Flying Thunder Wyvern\\\", \\\"Flying Sparks\\\") resembles a colubrid with a squirrel-like shape, covered in grayish-blue scales and white fur patches. Its tail has rows of spikes, and when fully charged, the fur on its back stands up. It shares similarities with Zinogre, being a thunder-element quadruped with a spiny tail and agility.\\n\\nTobi-Kadachi accumulates static electricity in its fur during battles, enhancing its attacks. The stronger it is, it can charge up at will and achieve a second charged state. Its gliding ability, similar to a flying squirrel, allows it to cover long distances. It can launch electrified hairs at foes, akin to its subspecies.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1157 cm - 1573 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":180,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":180,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":182,\"keys\":[\"Viper Tobi Kadachi\",\"Flying Poison Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Viper Tobi Kadachi\",\"content\":\"The Viper Tobi-Kadachi shares similarities with its standard counterpart, featuring a colubrid-like face, a squirrel-like body with fur patches along its back, and a bushy, spike-adorned tail. Its distinctive features include a color palette of brown, bronze, and burnt orange, with a yellowish-to-pale blue underside. Notably, it sports extra spikes on its tail, used as poisonous projectiles. The eyes of the Viper Tobi-Kadachi are golden yellow, unlike the red eyes of the standard species.\\n\\nViper Tobi-Kadachi inflicts potent poison and paralysis using its fangs and tail spikes. The tail spikes serve as projectiles for poisoning multiple targets, while the fangs induce paralysis. It retains the ability to glide with membranes between its limbs.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 1157 cm - 1573 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":181,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":181,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":183,\"keys\":[\"Odogaron\",\"Cruel Claw Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Odogaron\",\"content\":\"Odogaron (also called: \\\"Cruel Claw Wyvern\\\") is a swift, wolf-like, quadrupedal monster covered in red scales and bony protrusions resembling muscle and bone. Its double row of claws is used to inflict deep wounds on prey. After eating, red veins glow on its back. The bony tail can be used as a club.\\n\\nOdogaron is agile and swift, capable of rushing down prey and inflicting deep cuts with its powerful jaws and double claws. It often drags corpses back to its lair and enters a special enraged state after eating. In this state, red veins glow on its back, and it becomes more aggressive. Staggering Odogaron may result in immediate and aggressive retaliation.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Bleeding\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 541 cm - 1735 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":182,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":182,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":184,\"keys\":[\"Ebony Odogaron\",\"Wicked Claw Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ebony Odogaron\",\"content\":\"Ebony Odogaron has dark blue and jet black scales with blood-red, serrated claws. Its glowing red eyes and the black smoke emitted from its mouth give it a distinct appearance. The dragon element properties in its mouth are reminiscent of Savage Deviljho.\\n\\nEbony Odogaron is a relentless and precise hunter, always on the lookout for its next meal. It carries recent kills in its mouth to enhance its abilities. In combat, it uses its claws, tail, and powerful jaws to attack with precision. Unlike its regular counterpart, Ebony Odogaron can inflict Dragonblight on opponents through the smoke emitted from its mouth and by spitting dragon-infused chunks of flesh.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Bleeding\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1249 cm - 1722 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":183,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":183,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":185,\"keys\":[\"Wulg\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Wulg\",\"content\":\"ulgs greatly resemble a cross between a wolf and a badger, possessing a thick black and white striped pelt, a lithe frame and a long bushy tail. Their faces are long and tapering, and covered in black fur. Wulgs also posses long, blue, and slightly curved claws on their shins, which most of the time are buried in their fur.\\n\\nWulgs will attack hunters if they come across them, but won't directly hunt them.\\n\\nThey are capable of lunging and biting at foes, as well as performing an acrobatic grapple attack that requires hunters to move quickly lest they be stripped of their health.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nHeight: Small\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":184,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":184,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":186,\"keys\":[\"Malice Tiger Wyvern\",\"Devourer of the Rampage\",\"Wyvern of Malice\",\"Magnamalo\",\"Barbarous Beast\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Magnamalo\",\"content\":\"Magnamalo (Also called: \\\"Malice Tiger Wyvern\\\", \\\"Wyvern of Malice\\\", \\\"Barbarous Beast\\\", \\\"Devourer of the Rampage\\\") is a massive Fanged Wyvern resembling a tiger, with purple and yellow armor plates, a tigrine snout, foldable tusks, jagged yellow horns, and long ears. Its forelegs have large serrated blades, and its tail ends in a trident-like tip. When enraged, hidden bone blades spring out from its back.\\n\\nMagnamalo is an aggressive predator with strength, agility, and a blade-like tail for attacks. It produces volatile Hellfire gas by metabolizing bones, using it in various forms during combat. The gas becomes more explosive as the fight progresses. Magnamalo's high metabolism allows swift recovery from non-fatal wounds if there's enough food.\\n\\nMagnamalo is fiercely territorial and hostile, attacking both smaller monsters and hunters. Its high metabolism drives it to constantly seek prey to devour for sustenance.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Hellfireblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 1602 cm - 2276 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":185,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":185,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":187,\"keys\":[\"Malice Tiger Wyvern\",\"Devourer of the Rampage\",\"Wyvern of Malice\",\"Scorned Magnamalo\",\"Ultimate Malice\",\"Barbarous Beast\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Scorned Magnamalo\",\"content\":\"Scorned Magnamalo (Also called: \\\"Ultimate Malice\\\", \\\"Malice Tiger Wyvern\\\", \\\"Wyvern of Malice\\\", \\\"Barbarous Beast\\\", \\\"Devourer of the Rampage\\\") is a variant with elongated, oddly serrated arm-blades, larger fangs, and more jagged back shells that unfold when enraged. It lacks the right horn and eye, and its body is covered in volatile pink Hellfire. The dark purple color and glowing red scars resemble Apex Monsters in Kamura.\\n\\nScorned Magnamalo, fueled by years of battle scars, has enhanced physical prowess and perfected Hellfire attacks. It wields elongated arm-blades, concentrating Hellfire for deadly combos. In a \\\"Raging Hellfire\\\" state, the flames turn red, causing Dragonblight and heightened aggression.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Hellfireblight, Fireblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Water Element\\nLength: 1602 cm - 2276 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":186,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":186,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":188,\"keys\":[\"Larinoth\",\"Crying Neck Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Large Monster\",\"Fanged Wyvern\"],\"comment\":\"Larinoth\",\"content\":\"Larinoth (Also called: \\\"Crying Neck Wyvern\\\") is a large herbivorous monster with a distinctively long neck, rounded club-like tail, and spiked plating running along its back. Resembling sauropods, it shares similarities with the Brachiosaurus but lacks ties to any specific genus. The creature's plating is predominantly green, while the underbelly is cream-colored.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: None\\nLength: ~ 2151.59 / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":187,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":187,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":189,\"keys\":[\"Lunagaron\",\"Icy Wolf Wyvern\",\"Moonlight Nocturne\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lunagaron\",\"content\":\"Lunagaron (Also called: \\\" Icy Wolf Wyvern\\\", \\\"Moonlight Nocturne\\\") is a sizable, wolf-like Fanged Wyvern resembling New World counterparts like Odogaron and Tobi-Kadachi. Its cobalt scales have white edges, and during rage, ice spikes cover its body and claws.\\n\\nLunagaron showcases agility, climbing walls and rocks effortlessly. It regulates body temperature with a unique organ, forming ice armor for defense, freezing claws for enhanced attacks, and emitting freezing mist. Even in non-cold environments, Lunagaron's ice remains. When angered, it adopts a bipedal stance, becoming more aggressive and executing formidable claw attacks. Shattering its ice armor reverts it to quadrupedal form.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nLength: 1272 cm - 1739 cm / Height: Medium\\nFanged Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":188,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":188,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":190,\"keys\":[\"Fanged Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Fanged Wyvern\",\"content\":\"Fanged Wyverns are known for their quadrupedal structure, featuring wingless forelimbs larger than their hindlimbs. While some, like Odogaron and Tobi-Kadachi, anchor their weight downward, others, such as Great Jagras or Dodogama, may spread their limbs to the sides. These wyverns exhibit agility and speed, though some, like Great Jagras and Dodogama, are less nimble.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":189,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":189,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":191,\"keys\":[\"Lord of the Seas\",\"Lagiacrus\",\"Sea Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lagiacrus\",\"content\":\"The Lagiacrus (Also called: \\\"Sea Wyvern\\\", \\\"Lord of the Seas\\\") is a stocky, elongated reptile with a laterally-compressed tail, featuring a tapered snout, glossy orange-hued horns and back spines, and a dichotomous color scheme for camouflage. It has overlapping plate scales on the upper torso, blue scutes on the limbs, and a ribbed hood with electroreceptors. The front feet have five webbed digits, and the hind feet have four webbed toes. When a Lagiacrus is fully sunbathed, it turns a dry grayish-blue color and its dermal spikes turn brown. When it returns to the water, Lagiacrus regains a striking deep blue color and its spikes return to their original color of a very light beige.\\n\\nThe dermal spikes on its back glow white when it is using strong thunder attacks, and its mouth gurgles with Thunder when it is enraged.\\n\\nIt's most at home underwater, but is more than capable of fighting on land.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: 2330 cm - 3310 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":190,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":190,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":192,\"keys\":[\"Ivory Lagiacrus\",\"White Sea Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ivory Lagiacrus\",\"content\":\"Ivory Lagiacrus (Also called: \\\"White Sea Wyvern\\\") sports a briny white body, unlike the usual blue of Lagiacrus. In addition, the various knobs, spines and horns on its body are a deep blue, compared to the common Lagiacrus's brown and orange.\\n\\nIt has many enhanced and powerful thunder attacks that can cover a wider area than those of the common Lagiacrus.\\n\\nUnlike the other two species of Lagiacrus, Ivory Lagiacrus prefers a terrestrial lifestyle and spends very little of its time in the water.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element, Water Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 2516 cm - 3310 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":191,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":191,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":193,\"keys\":[\"Devil of the Sea\",\"Consumer of the World\",\"Dark Sea Wyvern\",\"Abyssal Lagiacrus\",\"Master of the Wave\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Abyssal Lagiacrus\",\"content\":\"The Abyssal Lagiacrus (Also called: \\\"Dark Sea Wyvern\\\", \\\"Master of the Wave\\\", \\\"Consumer of the World\\\", \\\"Devil of the Sea\\\") is notably larger than typical Lagiacrus, featuring a black bio-luminescent shell with vivid blue lights. It stands out with red glowing eyes, electric blue mouth, and prominent horns and spines on its head.\\n\\nAbyssal Lagiacrus maintains a perpetual fully charged state, emitting constant maximum-power glow from its spikes. It unleashes electric blasts akin to Ivory Lagiacrus and utilizes its serpentine motions to create disorienting underwater whirlpools, setting up hunters for potent attacks.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nLength: ~ 3969 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":192,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":192,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":194,\"keys\":[\"Ludroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ludroth\",\"content\":\"Ludroth, primarily yellow-green, move swiftly underwater with sinewy bodies and effective claws. Most are female, forming harems around the male Royal Ludroth, characterized by a distinctive sponge coating. Both genders display sponge-like growth, with unclear origins, possibly a co-evolved symbiotic relationship or unknown traits.\\n\\nLudroth spit mucus, causing Waterblight and slowing stamina recovery in hunters.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: ~ 412 cm / Height: Small\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":193,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":193,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":195,\"keys\":[\"Water Beast\",\"Mane Contender\",\"Royal Ludroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Royal Ludroth\",\"content\":\"Royal Ludroth (also called: \\\"Water Beast\\\", \\\"Mane Contender\\\"): Crowned crest, spongey yellow mane, yellow serpentine body, paddle-like hind legs, muscular front legs with black claws, shear-like jaw plates.\\n\\nRoyal Ludroth utilizes its absorbent mane to store water for various defenses, including spewing mucus globules and forcefully ejecting water at high speeds to repel nearby enemies. Adept swimmers, they excel as formidable aquatic hunters.\\n\\nAs the alpha male, Royal Ludroth leads a harem of females. Aggressive in nature, it fiercely defends against any perceived threats to itself or its clan.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1359 cm - 1931 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":194,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":194,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":196,\"keys\":[\"Purple Water Beast\",\"Purple Ludroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Purple Ludroth\",\"content\":\"The purple coloring is due to the large amounts of toxins stored in its body. It has pale, grey skin and bright orange claws and spikes.\\n\\nA large quantity of poison is stored in its large purple mane like a sponge. The Purple Ludroth (also called: \\\"Purple Water Beast\\\") can spit balls of poison mucus out of its mouth. It also releases a splash of poison from its mane by slamming into the ground.\\n\\nThe Purple Ludroth generally lives a solitary life free of any following of males or females. Unlike the common species, it is not known to spend time in the water.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1467 - 1933 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":195,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":195,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":197,\"keys\":[\"Uroktor\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Uroktor\",\"content\":\"Uroktor, akin to adult Agnaktor, can tunnel through solid volcanic rock. Distinguished by reddish-purple skin, it provides protection from heat and volcanic predators.\\n\\nUroktor, as minion monsters, move by burrowing and attack in three ways: drilling-jump from beneath, spitting fire while half-exposed, and rarely attempting a leviathan's double-bite when fully exposed on the ground.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: ~ 412 cm / Height: Small\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":196,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":196,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":198,\"keys\":[\"Fire Pike Wyvern\",\"Agnaktor\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Agnaktor\",\"content\":\"Agnaktor (Also called: \\\"Fire Pike Wyvern\\\"), akin to Lagiacrus, is a lava-swimming Leviathan with the ability to tunnel through volcanic rock. Its lava-like armor hardens when cooled and softens when heated. Featuring a drill-like beak with needle-like teeth, Agnaktor closely resembles Uroktor, with differences in size and the ability to make magma stick to its body. Both can fire blasts of fire, with Agnaktor capable of a coherent beam.\\n\\nAgnaktor charges through rock, emitting an orange beam. Its lava armor, initially orange-red, cools to black and hardens without activity. It can tunnel through ceilings as well.\\n\\nAgnaktor are quite aggressive, challenging all others that encroach on its habitat, due to the fact that it has no natural predators at an adult age. The only threat that it encounters is if a monster challenges it for territory or food.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 2416 - 3421 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":197,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":197,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":199,\"keys\":[\"Freeze Pike Wyvern\",\"Glacial Agnaktor\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Glacial Agnaktor\",\"content\":\"Tje Glacial Agnaktor (Also called: \\\"Freeze Pike Wyvern\\\") has an icy armor that hardens when burrowing and softens over time. It features a longer, harder, and sharper beak, ideal for digging through the ice of the Tundra.\\n\\nIt attacks with a beam composed of ice and water, similar to the normal Agnaktor's fire beam, that inflicts Waterblight. Unlike the normal Agnaktor, it can sweep the beam from side to side as well as moving it in circles.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element, Water Element\\nAilment: Iceblight, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nLength: 2198 - 3176 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":198,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":198,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":200,\"keys\":[\"Mermaid Wyvern\",\"Somnacanth\",\"Soporific Siren\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Somnacanth\",\"content\":\"Somnacanth (Also called: \\\"Mermaid Wyvern\\\", \\\"Soporific Siren\\\") has yellowish scales, humanoid features, and distinctive purple fins. Bioluminescent patches adorn its body, including eyes, mouth, throat seams, and tail base.\\n\\nSomnacanth, often seen swimming on its back or standing on its tail, is territorial and highly aggressive. It produces sleep-inducing powder, deploying it as a ranged cone or area-wide cloud. It attacks by jumping, slamming, and launching dart-like quills. Standing on its tail during combat, it utilizes its hard belly to crack shells, each with unique effects like explosion, directional flash, or healing mist for nearby hunters.\\n\\nElement: None \\nAilment: Sleep, Stun, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1390 - 1899 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":199,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":199,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":201,\"keys\":[\"Ice Mermaid Wyvern\",\"Seductive Siren\",\"Aurora Somnacanth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Aurora Somnacanth\",\"content\":\"Aurora Somnacanth (also called: \\\"Ice Mermaid Wyvern\\\", \\\"Seductive Siren\\\"), resembling Somnacanth, has a pale yellow body, ice-blue fins with a dark purple gradient, and white bioluminescence. Frost forms on its head-crest and tail, adding to its distinct appearance.\\n\\nAurora Somnacanth, with a Cryo Sac, unleashes ice attacks, including a beam and frost explosions. It spends more time on land, using icy mist to freeze surroundings for swift movement, sharing abilities with Barioth and Goss Harag.\\n\\nAurora Somnacanth is an aggressive monster using a siren-like voice to lure and freeze prey. It preys on small monsters like Izuchi and clashes with Aknosom, chasing it away due to the flame disruption of its cold air.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1390 - 1899 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":200,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":200,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":202,\"keys\":[\"Lantern Fish Wyvern\",\"Gobul\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gobul\",\"content\":\"Gobul (Also called: \\\"Lantern Fish Wyvern\\\"), a distinct Leviathan, combines angler, stingray, puffer fish, and catfish traits. It has purple scales, a bio-luminescent lure on its forehead, and a massive, tooth-filled mouth. Retractable spines adorn its back, and its tail quills can induce paralysis upon contact.\\n\\nGobul swallows prey whole with its massive mouth, using its blinding lure and camouflage for hunting. When enraged, it puffs up to appear more intimidating.\\n\\nGobul is generally passive until provoked, often lying under the river bed to mimic a plant with only its whiskers exposed. While mostly aquatic, it occasionally ventures onto land without pursuing prey.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Paralysis, Stun\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1562 - 2844 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":201,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":201,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":203,\"keys\":[\"Nibelsnarf\",\"Latent Mouth Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nibelsnarf\",\"content\":\"Nibelsnarf (also called: \\\"Latent Mouth Wyvern\\\"), adept at burrowing and disguising as sand dunes, resembles Gobul. With a salamander-like body, colorful underbelly, and razor-sharp teeth, it swims in sand, preying on Rhenoplos and Apceros. Hunters can target its uvula, a fragile weak spot, during attacks like sand spewing, charging, and a leaping bite.\\n\\nNibelsnarf uses a \\\"Wind Tunnel\\\" attack to expel sand and cause Waterblight. It can move during this attack and surprise attackers with a sand cloud. When staggered, it can be pulled out of the ground, similar to Gobul. Nibelsnarf devours bombs, getting stunned when they explode inside it. Failure to pull it out results in a damaging spinning attack.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1808 - 4693 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":202,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":202,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":204,\"keys\":[\"Epioth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Epioth\",\"content\":\"Epioth, fish-like monsters, feature four flippers with spiked tips, medium-sized fins on their back, and fish-shaped tails with small spikes. Their coloration includes a green top half, white bellies and necks, and orange accents on fins, flippers, and sides.\\n\\nEpioth, timid creatures, usually flee when attacked but may retaliate with weak slams and tail slaps. They swim underwater and surface occasionally, providing moments for hunters to attack when they pause.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nLength: ~ 353 cm / Height: Small\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":203,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":203,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":205,\"keys\":[\"Bubble Fox Wyvern\",\"Bewitching Dancer\",\"Mizutsune\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Mizutsune\",\"content\":\"Mizutsune (Also called: \\\"Bubble Fox Wyvern\\\", \\\"Bewitching Dancer\\\"), a unique Leviathan, has a slender body with dark purple fur on its chest, underbelly, legs, and tail. Fish-like scales cover its body, and it features pink fins with yellow markings on its head, back, and tail. Swift movement on land is facilitated by its distinctive feet. Females are duller in color with shorter fins and dark black fur.\\n\\nMizutsune secretes soapy fluid for agile sliding and offensive tactics: hindering bubbles and pressurized water jets like Plesioth.\\n\\nMizutsune is generally non-aggressive but can become violent if provoked. During mating season, males go berserk, attacking anyone in their path, prompting hunters to intervene. Females are friendlier and humans, Wyverians, as well as Lynians can approach them and cuddle with them.\\n\\nElement: Water\\nAilment: Waterblight, Bubble\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 565 - 2356 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":204,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":204,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":206,\"keys\":[\"Violet Mizutsune\",\"Dance of Eldritch Flame\",\"Blazing Fox Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Violet Mizutsune\",\"content\":\"Violet Mizutsune features whitish-lilac scales with indigo streaks, indigo fins, and black fur. In its empowered state, the fur glows faintly blue. As a Rare Species, it is slightly larger than a regular Mizutsune.\\n\\nViolet Mizutsune's unique fluid is flammable, creating deadly flames. It launches homing flaming bubbles, igniting streams, and explosive puddles. Increasing fluid secretion engulfs it in white-hot flames, enhancing attacks until disrupted by damage.\\n\\nViolet Mizutsune sleeps when not fighting but reacts violently to intruders. It easily defeats monsters like Tigrex but contends with Apex Monsters, other Rare Species, and Elder Dragons for territory.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Defense Down\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nLength: 1738 - 2269 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":205,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":205,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":207,\"keys\":[\"Soulseer Mizutsune\",\"Soulseer\",\"Heavenly Eye\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Soulseer Mizutsune\",\"content\":\"Soulseer Mizutsune (also called: \\\"Soulseer\\\", \\\"Heavenly Eye\\\"), akin to the common variant but larger, features paler fur and coats its front claws and tail in a substance, intensifying their reddish hue during combat. Distinctive scars run across its face, causing blindness, yet its left eye opens and glows with a blue flame when enraged, likely from past battles.\\n\\nBlind but perceptive through bubbles, Soulseer Mizutsune releases expanding spirals of bubbles while calm, slowing its movements. Contact with these bubbles triggers rage, making it more aggressive and launching blue, fireblight-inflicting bubbles. Coating its front claws or tail in dark red bubbles increases vulnerability and damage output, granting an attack boost to hunters hit by them. It employs a spiral drill rush and body slam attacks, especially when enraged.\\n\\nElement: Water Element, Fire Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Bubble, Fireblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: ~ 2792 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":206,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":206,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":208,\"keys\":[\"Apex Mizutsune\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Apex Mizutsune\",\"content\":\"Apex Mizutsune, has a darker tone, wounds, purple arm fur, and a deep blue torso and tail. Enraged, its head and back crests become redder.\\n\\nApex Mizutsune is highly aggressive, attacking on sight with bubbles infused with hellfire similar to Magnamalo. The bubbles function like those of Soulseer Mizutsune. In its enraged state, it employs a powerful tail uppercut and a move reminiscent of Soulseer, creating orbiting bubbles while shooting a spiraling water jet.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Hellfireblight, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element, Iceblight\\nLength: 1456 - 2356 cm / Height: Medium\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":207,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":207,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":209,\"keys\":[\"Hermit of the Swamp\",\"Almudron\",\"Elderly Mud Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Large Monster\",\"Magma Almudron\",\"Leviathan\"],\"comment\":\"Almudron\",\"content\":\"Almudron (also called: \\\"Elderly Mud Wyvern\\\", \\\"Hermit of the Swamp\\\"), a massive bog-dwelling Leviathan, has a gray shell on its dorsal side and legs, featuring darker highlights. It has scaly skin in shades of gray, creamy yellow, and pinkish red, with a wide, pink underbelly. Its head has mammalian-like traits, and it sports massive curved claws on its front legs. The prominent feature is its lengthy tail with feather-like appendages used for mud attacks.\\n\\nAlmudron wields mud as a weapon, creating waves with its tail and bursting from muddy soil. It forms mud walls and piles using a golden fluid, trapping and draining the health of stuck hunters.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Muddy\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Ice Element\\nLength: 2425 - 3368 cm / Height: Large\\nLeviathan\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":208,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":208,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":210,\"keys\":[\"Scorching Mud\",\"Melting Elderly Wyvern\",\"Magma Almudron\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Magma Almudron\",\"content\":\"Magma Almudron (also called: \\\"Melting Elderly Wyvern\\\", \\\"Scorching Mud\\\") is bluish gray and crimson in color, with a red glow that can be seen through the seams between its shell. It is noticeably smaller than the normal Almudron.\\n\\nMagma Almudron uses its tail to spread magma, melting the ground. It can dig into volcanic terrain, heating its body parts, and creates magma pillars before explosive eruptions. Holding a magma-mud ball with its tail, it uses it as a bludgeon against foes, causing a ground-shaking explosion upon impact.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element \\