\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":212,\"keys\":[\"Delex\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Delex\",\"content\":\"Similar to Cephalos, Delex possess the ability to \\\"swim\\\" through sand, expelling small sand blasts from their mouths that may inflict Waterblight. Their nimbleness makes them challenging targets for slower weapons. Found in groups of six or seven, they hunt small animals and scavenge remains from larger desert-dwelling monsters, like Jhen Mohran, often appearing in fights with such creatures.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight \\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 203 cm - 405 cm / Height: Small\\nPiscine Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":211,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":211,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":213,\"keys\":[\"Sinister Swamp Shadow\",\"Jyuratodus\",\"Mud Fish Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Jyuratodus\",\"content\":\"Jyuratodus (Also called: \\\"Mud Fish Wyvern\\\", \\\"Sinister Swamp Shadow\\\"), akin to Lavasioth, is a bipedal coelacanth fish covered in mud and sludge instead of hardened lava.\\n\\nJyuratodus defends with mud, trapping hunters with watery sludge. Its swimming leaves solid mud platforms. Like Barroth, it rolls in mud for protection against damage and Thunder Element. In a turf war with Barroth, both monsters suffer damage. While passive in its territory, disturbance triggers aggression.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight, Muddy\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1327 cm - 1885 cm / Height: Medium\\nPiscine Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":212,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":212,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":214,\"keys\":[\"Water Wyvern\",\"Plesioth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Plesioth\",\"content\":\"Plesioth, wyvern-like bipedal monsters, have webbed feet, a paddle-like tail, and shiny, fish-like scales. They boast a mouth with shark-like teeth, glowing yellow eyes, and flexible fins on their head and back.\\n\\nPlesioth unleash pressurized water jets and use their size to crush foes. In water, they are agile and lethal, showcasing their adept swimming abilities.\\n\\nPlesioth are ambush predators, adapted to stalking prey from the water and attacking by surprise. They can occasionally be seen on land.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight, Sleep\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1991 cm - 3877 cm / Height: Large\\nPiscine Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":213,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":213,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":215,\"keys\":[\"Green Water Wyvern\",\"The Tide\",\"Green Plesioth\",\"Master of the Giant Lake\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Large Monster\",\"Plesioth\",\"Piscine Wyvern\"],\"comment\":\"Green Plesioth\",\"content\":\"Green Plesioth (also called: \\\" Green Water Wyvern\\\", \\\"The Tide\\\", \\\"Master of the Giant Lake\\\") shares the same body structure as the common species but stands out with deep green scales, complemented by white and purple striped spines and fins.\\n\\nGreen Plesioth is a skilled swimmer, particularly adept in underwater combat, and demonstrates enhanced water sac control compared to the common species.\\n\\nGreen Plesioth is an aggressive wyvern with the ability to detect multiple hunters. It shares a love for frogs with the common species and goes ashore to attack when enraged.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight, Sleep\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 2125 cm - 3877 cm / Height: Large\\nPiscine Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":214,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":214,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":216,\"keys\":[\"Cephalos\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Chephalos\",\"content\":\"Cephalos have streamlined, flat bodies designed for sand swimming, featuring hammer-shaped heads with upward-facing eyes. Their brown and beige coloration aids in desert sand camouflage.\\n\\nThese monsters are surprisingly social, swimming through the loose sand and hunting in packs. They are predatory, and can work together to defeat creatures many times their size.\\n\\nMildly aggressive, they can become a nuisance when fighting other monsters.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: ~ 465 cm / Height: Small\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":215,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":215,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":217,\"keys\":[\"Cephadrome\",\"Sand Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Cephadrome\",\"content\":\"Cephadrome (Also called: \\\"Sand Wyvern\\\") exhibit yellow eyes, yellow or pink fins, and blue or purple scales covered in sand, giving them a brownish-black appearance. Their flat, diamond-shaped head, fins, and tail aid in sand propulsion.\\n\\nCephadrome, cautious in combat, retreat by diving into the sand. Their attacks include hipchecks, tail swipes, and sand stream shots. They can paralyze prey with their dorsal fin while swimming. Sonic bombs can startle them out of the sand due to their excellent hearing, akin to the Plesioth.\\n\\nCephadrome are very aggressive, but will assume evasive maneuvers if they sense that the threat is too dangerous.\\n\\nElement: Water Element \\nAilment: Waterblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 889 cm - 2097 cm / Height: Large\\nPiscine Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":216,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":216,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":218,\"keys\":[\"Lava Wyvern\",\"Lavasioth\",\"Lava Fish\",\"Lava Shit\",\"Lavashit\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lavasioth\",\"content\":\"Lavasioth (also called: \\\"Lava Wyvern\\\", or hatefully: \\\"Lavashit\\\", \\\"Lava Shit\\\", \\\"Lava Fish\\\"), resembling a bipedal coelacanth fish, is covered in hardened lava, forming a robust outer shell. It has dorsal fins, pectoral fins, pelvic fins, and a long tail for swimming through lava. The fish-like head features rounded features, large circular eyes, and a mouth with sharp, needle-like fangs. Its powerful hind-legs end in fins and can support it on land.\\n\\nLavasioth's attacks resemble those of Plesioth, including firing large magma balls that scatter into smaller rocks upon impact. It also uses its weight for slamming and crushing attacks against hunters.\\n\\nLavasioth, a rare Piscine Wyvern, resides in lava and fiercely defends its territory, attacking intruders on sight.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element \\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Water Element\\nLength: 1581 cm - 3476 cm / Height: Medium\\n