,\"comment\":\"Najarala\",\"content\":\"Najarala (Also called: \\\"Twisting Snake Wyvern\\\") is a sizable Snake Wyvern featuring vibrant green skin decorated with large orange-yellow plates on its back and tail. Its elongated, serpent-like body includes small yet fully functional fore- and hindlimbs, facilitating movement on varied terrain. The creature also possesses a prominent beak resembling that of a parrot, complemented by a pair of small tusks.\\n\\nNajarala is a burrowing Snake Wyvern that paralyzes foes with venomous fangs, uses tail plates for deafening noise or stunning shards, and constricts victims with its large body.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Water Element\\nLength: 3568 cm - 5068 cm / Height: Large\\nSnake Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":220,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":220,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":222,\"keys\":[\"Tidal Najarala\",\"Water Snake Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tidal Najarala\",\"content\":\"Tidal Najarala features a blue, yellow and grey hide lined with rows of purple and green spines.\\n\\nUnlike the common relative Najarala, this subspecies can spit watery globules at its victims. It also develops a new attack using its shedable scales. During this attack it shoots out a water ball which then quickly homes in on unwary hunters by rebounding through the scales left on the ground.\\n\\nElement: Water\\nAilment: Paralysis, Waterelement\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: ~ 5271 cm / Height: Large\\nSnake Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":221,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":221,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":223,\"keys\":[\"Remorba\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Remorba\",\"content\":\"Small but agile flying wyverns that seek out weakened creatures to attack. Often seen near elder dragons, they're considered a portent of disaster. Originally classified as flying wyverns, after further research they were reclassified as snake wyverns.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element\\nLength: ~ 406 cm / Height: Small\\nSnake Wyvern\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"