tant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":229,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":229,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":231,\"keys\":[\"Demon Frog\",\"Tetsucabra\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tetsucabra\",\"content\":\"Tetsucabra (also called: \\\"Demon Frog\\\") is a large Amphibian with orange and indigo coloration, featuring large tusks and molars for crushing prey.\\n\\nTetsucabra can lift and throw large boulders with it's tusks, using them as shields or to block paths. It crushes boulders with powerful jaws, sending shards flying, and can spit a stamina-draining substance.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Fatigue\\nWeakness: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 632 cm - 1582 cm / Height: Large\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":230,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":230,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":232,\"keys\":[\"Berserk Tetsucabra\",\"Wild Demon Frog\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Berserk Tetsucabra\",\"content\":\"Berserk Tetsucabra (also called: \\\"Wild Demon Frog\\\") has a dark green body with a grey tail and brown tusks due to the soot and gas from the explosions caused by explosive rocks. The monster's face will also become orange from each explosion as well.\\n\\nWhile the attacks displayed so far look similar enough to the normal Tetsucabras; this subspecies is clearly more violent and destructive. They are able to easily crush explosive rocks with their jaws to create a wide-radius explosion.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Fatigue\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 632 cm - 1582 cm / Height: Large\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":231,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":231,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":233,\"keys\":[\"Evil Faced Star\",\"Drilltusk Tetsucabra\",\"Rock Piercer\",\"Drilltusk\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Drilltusk Tetsucabra\",\"content\":\"Drilltusk Tetsucabra (also called: \\\"Drilltusk\\\", \\\"Evil Faced Star\\\", \\\"Rock Piercer\\\") are very close to normal Tetsucabra in appearance, but bear a few distinctions from them. A Drilltusk's horns are longer and more pointed, similar to how its tusks are much longer than a normal Tetsucabra's. It also possesses longer fangs, and one tusk is always longer than the other. Unlike normal ones, Drilltusk Tetsucabra have more blue markings and scales toward their anterior. Drilltusk Tetsucabra loves to go on rampages as well.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Fatigue, Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1437 cm - 1649 cm / Height: Large\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":232,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":232,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":234,\"keys\":[\"Zamite\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Zamite\",\"content\":\"Zamite are small, shark-like creatures with rows of sharp teeth. They can grow larger and develop legs by ingesting bodily fluids during battle.\\n\\nZamite behave similar to Giggi in the manner of aggressively attacking any possible food source and draining them of their vital fluids.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight, Lifedrain\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 187 cm - 373 cm / Height: Small\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":233,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":233,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":235,\"keys\":[\"Monster Shark\",\"Zamtrios\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Zamtrios\",\"content\":\"Zamtrios (also called: \\\"Monster Shark\\\") is a large, quadrupedal monster with shark-like features, grey-blue skin, and yellow fins. It can encase itself in ice-like armor with spines and horns. As the adult form of Zamite, it has powerful limbs and elastic skin for inflation abilities.\\n\\nZamtrios is a predator that surprises prey with attacks from beneath sea ice. It secretes a reactive fluid that solidifies into ice-like armor when threatened. It shoots powerful water torrents, travels beneath ice for ambushes, and encases itself in an icy armor, using the fluid to immobilize prey. It can swell up, rolling and jumping to crush targets.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element, Water Element\\nAilment: Iceblight, Waterblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1367 cm - 3039 cm / Height: Large\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":234,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":234,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":236,\"keys\":[\"Tiger Shark\",\"Tigerstripe Zamtrios\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tigerstripe Zamtrios\",\"content\":\" It has an orange-brown body color with some red shades mixed in it while fins and belly are more blueish.\\n\\nThe sandy Tigerstripe Zamtrios retains the same attacks as its arctic counterpart but can use them more efficiently. It can immediately inflate and start a rolling attack without taking damage first. Additionally, it can leap in its inflated form, covering a larger area. The monster can shoot a stream of water to deflate itself at will. It can also spit paralyzing fluid but lacks the ability to create armor around its body.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Ice Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 1458 cm - 1899 cm / Height: Large\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":235,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":235,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":237,\"keys\":[\"Amphibious Wrestler\",\"Tetranodon\",\"Kappa Frog\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Tetranodon\",\"content\":\"Tetranadon is an Amphibian with an inflatable belly and a turtle-like shell on its back. It has algae-like fur on its head, front legs, shell, and tail, along with orange eyes with horizontal pupils. The creature has a toothless, platypus-like beak and webbed feet. Tetranadon walks on all fours when its belly is not inflated, but when it swallows debris, its belly inflates, and it stands on its hindlegs.\\n\\nTetranadon inflates its belly by swallowing gravel, becoming sluggish but powerful. It battles Arzuros, unsuccessfully trying to swallow it, and easily defeats Lagombi and Volvidon. It faces challenges from predators like Anjanath, Goss Harag, and Seething Bazelgeuse. Inflated Tetranadon exhibits sumo-like attacks, causing quakes and high jumps. Damaging it can knock it out of the bloated state, leaving it vulnerable.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nLength: 858 cm - 1206 cm / Height: Medium\\nAmphibian\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":236,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":236,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":238,\"keys\":[\"Amphibians\",\"Amphibian\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Amphibian\",\"content\":\"Amphibians have frog-like bodies with strong back legs, muscular forelegs, and inhabit diverse environments. They are generally carnivorous in nature.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":237,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":237,\"probability\":100,\"