atch_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":240,\"keys\":[\"Altaroth\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Altaroth\",\"content\":\"Altaroth have sacs on their backs to store absorbed resources. When killed in this state, they drop a shiny item based on what they've consumed. Hunters can intercept them, force specific consumables, and gain corresponding items. Sac swelling indicates consumption, with colors signaling different contents.\\n\\nAltaroth can shoot a greenish-yellowish liquid from their abdomens, which will inflict a temporary defense drop. Aside from that, they will use their large mantibles to attack.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Defense Down, Paralysis\\nWeakness: None\\nLength: ~ 148 cm / Height: Tiny\\nNeopteron\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":239,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":239,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":241,\"keys\":[\"Vespoid\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Vespoid\",\"content\":\"Vespoids are yellow-and-purple wasp-like insects roughly the size of a housecat. They have barbed stingers at the end of their abdomens, and fly using two pairs of wings.\\n\\nThey are known to be a nuisance for hunters, due to their stings that cause hunters to flinch, resulting in them being exposed to any further attacks. Their stingers are loaded with a neuro-toxin that can paralyze foes.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: None\\nLength: ~ 136 cm / Height: Tiny\\nNeopteron\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":240,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":240,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":242,\"keys\":[\"Vespoid Queen\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Vespoid Queen\",\"content\":\"The Vespoid Queen looks similar to the average Vespoid but is several times larger, with a more pronounced abdomen and giant, rainbow coloured wings. She has a ridged exoskeleton covering her soft innards and she has a crown-like structure atop her head.\\n\\nShe has a large stinger on her tail that releases a gas which inflicts the Defense Down ailment. When sprayed with the Vespoid Queen's gas, the Vespoids in the area become much more aggressive.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Defense Down, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nLength: ~ 691 cm / Height: Small\\nNeopteron\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"inse