e\",\"content\":\"Ahtal-Ka compensates for its lack of physical strength by using the golden silk it produces to bind steel beams to its back, which it throws at enemies. Even without these beams, it remains a dangerous opponent, attacking with sharp claws and emitting a pheromone that reduces hunters' defense. When cornered, it can pull the massive Ahtal Nesto from the ground, controlling it like a puppet to crush foes. In this state, it utilizes the strength of its creation to generate quakes and immobilize hunters with silk.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":252,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":252,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":254,\"keys\":[\"Ahtal-Ka\",\"Ahtal Nesto\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"Round two\",\"round two\",\"Second Round\",\"phase two\",\"second round\",\"Second Phase\",\"second phase\",\"Phase two\"],\"comment\":\"Ahtal-Ka Phase Two\",\"content\":\"After sustaining enough damage, the Ahtal Nesto disassembles, and Ahtal-Ka resumes normal combat. During this phase, it binds a Dragonator to its back, throwing it like a spear at enemies. Additionally, using its golden silk, Ahtal-Ka can lift up to three Dragonators into the air and hurl them at hunters.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":253,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":253,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":255,\"keys\":[\"Ahtal-Ka\",\"Ahtal Nesto\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"third phase\",\"Round three\",\"round three\",\"Third Phase\",\"phase three\",\"three round\",\"Third Round\",\"Phase three\"],\"comment\":\"Ahtal-Ka Phase Three\",\"content\":\"When significantly damaged, Ahtal-Ka retreats to the center of the area, summoning the Ahtal Nesto once again. In this phase, it can directly attack hunters on its back, using the machine's \\\"tail\\\" to throw them off or expelling pheromones from a small cocoon.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":254,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":254,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":256,\"keys\":[\"Ahtal-Ka\",\"Ahtal Nesto\"],\"secondary_keys\":[\"round four\",\"phase four\",\"Phase four\",\"Round four\",\"fourth round\",\"Fourth Round\",\"fourth phase\",\"Fourth Phase\"],\"comment\":\"Ahtal-Ka Phase Four\",\"content\":\"In the final phase, after the Ahtal Nesto is destroyed, Ahtal-Ka emerges with a massive wheel on its back. It covers the area with silk, creating traps for hunters. Ahtal-Ka fights using the wheel, moving quickly and swinging it around. Additionally, it can pull three Dragonators from the ground, spinning them around to deal significant damage to hunters.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":255,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":255,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":257,\"keys\":[\"Neopterons\",\"Neopteron\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Neopteron\",\"content\":\"Neopterons are insectoid monsters with rigid carapaces, varying in size from tiny to enormous. Some can fly, while others cannot. They are highly susceptible to poison and fire but have resistance to the Dragon Element. Materials from Neopterons are often used to craft sharp weapons.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":256,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":256,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":258,\"keys\":[\"Shadow Spider\",\"Nerscylla\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nerscylla\",\"content\":\"Nerscylla is a large arachnid with a white body, orange claws, and crystalized poison spikes. It has retractable jaws for a poisonous bite and can produce sticky webbing to trap prey. It wears Gypceros hide.\\n\\nNerscylla (also called: \\\"Shadow Spider\\\") is adaptable and uses its silk to swing and capture prey. Its web is durable and sticky, making escape difficult. The stinger at its abdomen contains a tranquilizing fluid, causing Sleep status, or Deadly Poison in higher ranks.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison, Sleep, Webbed\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nSize: 833 cm - 1126 cm / Height: Medium\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":257,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":257,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":259,\"keys\":[\"Corpse Spider\",\"Shrouded Nerscylla\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shrouded Nerscylla\",\"content\":\"Shrouded Nerscylla (Also called: \\\"Corpse Spider\\\") is similar to the common counterpart but has a dark gray body with white stripes, purple markings, yellow underside, and turquoise hairs. It wears a Khezu hide instead of Gypceros. Its unique ability may result from its diet of Khezu, similar to the common Nerscylla's poison secretion from Gypceros feeding.\\n\\nShrouded Nerscylla can inflict paralysis with its back spikes and claws, and seems to demonstrate a mastery of web traversal, able to change direction mid-air by swinging on a different thread.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison, Noxious Poison, Paralysis, Webbed\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 389 cm - 1188 cm / Height: Medium\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":258,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":258,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":260,\"keys\":[\"Rachnoid\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rachnoid\",\"content\":\"Rachnoid are Temnocerans that resemble a mix between jumping spiders and ticks. They have large web-spun orbs covering their backs that closely resemble the egg sack found on adult Rakna Kadaki.\\n\\nRachnoids are aggressive creatures using claws and fiery bursts. They shoot sticky webs like Rakna's and often move in small groups when not with their mother.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Webbed\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nSize: Small\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":259,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":259,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":261,\"keys\":[\"Wandering Widow\",\"Empress Spider\",\"Rakna-Kadaki\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rakna-Kadaki\",\"content\":\"Rakna-Kadaki (also called: \\\"Empress Spider\\\", \\\"Wandering Widow\\\") are Temnocerans covered in spikes with an extendable neck. They have a purple carapace, eight legs, and distinctive burgundy pedipalps. Rachnoid offspring look like silk-covered balls with legs and spikes.\\n\\nRakna-Kadaki can spit silk, using it to bind prey and for various attacks. They wear their silk like a gown, carrying their babies and sending them for coordinated attacks.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Webbed\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 771 cm - 1071 cm / Height: Medium\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":260,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":260,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":262,\"keys\":[\"Pyrantula\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Pyrantula\",\"content\":\"The young of Pyre Rakna-Kadaki, Pyrantula look identical to Rachnoids and have light gray bodies with yellow eyes and glowing orange webbing on their backs.\\n\\nPyrantulas, explosive creatures with Blastblight-inducing gas, serve as weapons for their mother, the Pyre Rakna-Kadaki. The queen scatters them onto the battlefield or connects them with webs, creating explosive fuses. Pyrantulas are aggressive and follow the queen's commands, attacking intruders near their territory.\\n\\nElement: Fire\\nAilment: Fireblight, Blastblight, Webbed\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nSize: Small\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":261,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":261,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":263,\"keys\":[\"Blazing Empress Spider\",\"Pyre Rakna-Kadaki\",\"Parching Puppeteer\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Pyre Rakna-Kadaki\",\"content\":\"Pyre Rakna-Kadaki (also called: \\\"Blazing Empress Spider\\\", \\\"Parching Puppeteer\\\") is similar in appearance to a standard Rakna-Kadaki, but with several key differences; her body is now light gray with glowing orange hooks, and her webbing is now black. Her horns are now much longer, giving her a demonic appearance.\\n\\nThe Pyre Rakna-Kadaki employs explosive webs, inflicting Blastblight and fire, utilizing her Pyrantula offspring strategically. She commands Pyrantulas with a unique sound organ, coordinating advanced attacks, including setting up \\\"fuse bomb\\\" explosions.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Blastblight, Webbed\\nWeakness: Water Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 771 cm - 1071 cm / Height: Medium\\nTemnoceran\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":262,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":262,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":264,\"keys\":[\"Temnoceran\",\"Temnocerans\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Temnoceran\",\"content\":\"Temnocerans, a class of monsters, exhibit arachnoid traits like silk production. While most have six limbs like Neopterons or Carapaceons, certain Temnocerans, like Rakna-Kadaki, feature eight limbs.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":263,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":263,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":265,\"keys\":[\"Hermitaur\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Hermitaur\",\"content\":\"Hermaitaur are hermit crab-like monsters with red carapaces and a thick white shell. As they grow into Daimyo Hermitaur, they replace their shells with Monoblos or Black Diablos skulls. Hermitaurs are related to Ceanataur, blue Carapaceons found in volcanic regions.\\n\\nWhen undisturbed, Hermitaurs can be observed sifting through sand with their claws, likely in search of food. They may also lie in wait under the ground, ambushing passing prey or hunters by lunging from hiding. Burrowed Hermitaurs reveal their presence through periodic puffs of dust.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 156 cm / Size: Small\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":264,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":264,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":266,\"keys\":[\"Daimyo Hermitaur\",\"Shield Crab\",\"Shelled Sovereign\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Daimyo Hermitaur\",\"content\":\"Daimyo Hermitaur (also called: \\\"Shield Crab\\\", \\\"Shelled Sovereign\\\") has a large, crab-like body. It is covered in a red and white carapace and wears the skull of a Monoblos as a protective shell. It has broad, shield-like claws and long antennae.\\n\\nIt can use its claws as shields to defend itself from attackers, and, as with the Monoblos, can also use them to dig into the earth in order to attack foes from below. It can shoot pressurized jets of water and can use its massive weight to crush enemies.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nSize: 450 cm - 1451 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":265,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":265,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":267,\"keys\":[\"Plum Daimyo Hermitaur\",\"Shield Crab\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Plum Daimyo Hermitaur\",\"content\":\"Plum Daimyo Hermitaur (also called: \\\"Shield Crab\\\") sports a purple and white carapace, and wears a Diablos skullshell instead of a Monoblos skullshell. Unlike its red counterpart, the Plum Daimyo Hermitaur is weak against Ice, rather than Thunder. The horns on its shell can be broken, just like those of a Diablos.\\n\\nMuch like its cousin, the Plum Daimyo Hermitaur is docile until provoked or aggravated. Its territory is expansive and thus impossible for it to defend, leading it to be something of a nomad, wandering from place to place in search of food.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Lement\\nSize: 247 cm - 1346 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":266,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":266,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":268,\"keys\":[\"Crab Ramparts\",\"Spearbreaker\",\"Stonefist\",\"Stonefist Hermitaur\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Stonefist Hermitaur\",\"content\":\"The Stonefist Hermitaur (also called: \\\"Stonefist\\\", \\\"Crab Ramparts\\\", \\\"Spearbreaker\\\") is a Daimyo Hermitaur with an enlarged left pincer which doubles as a sturdy black shield. Its armor causes blades to shatter, and for shots to bounce off, filling the Hunter with holes instead. Requires special permission to hunt.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nSize: 1449 cm - 1793 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":267,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":267,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":269,\"keys\":[\"Ceanataur\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ceanataur\",\"content\":\"Ceanataur are similar in appearance to the Hermitaur with sharper claws, leg stubs and a higher-edge shell. The shell on its back was actually grown by the Ceanataur itself.\\n\\nThe Ceanataur is highly dangerous, known for spitting a small ball of poisonous fluid at foes. It may wait beneath the ground for prey or hunters, jumping out and striking when they walk over. The Ceanataur is considered even more aggressive than the Hermitaur.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Poison\\nWeakness: Thunder Element\\nLength: 283 cm / Size: Small\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":268,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":268,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":270,\"keys\":[\"Final Flash\",\"Sickle Crab\",\"Shogun Ceanataur\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shogun Ceanataur\",\"content\":\"Shogun Ceanataur (Also called: \\\"Sickle Crab\\\", \\\"Final Flash\\\") has a blue carapace, knife-shaped head, and lengthy antennae. Its folding claws act as sickles, extending in rage mode for increased reach. It inhabits various shells, including a Gravios skull, a snail-like shell, and an unknown wyvern skull.\\n\\nShogun Ceanataur can shoot pressurized water and climb on walls. It also defends itself by spraying urine on enemies from the ceiling.\\n\\nShogun Ceanataur is highly aggressive and defends itself vigorously when threatened. If any or all of its claws are broken, it remains in a permanent rage mode until it dies or the quest ends.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Bleeding\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 586 cm - 1294 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":269,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":269,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":271,\"keys\":[\"Terra Shogun Ceanataur\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Terra Shogun Ceanataur\",\"content\":\"Terra Shogun Ceanataur, considered a Subspecies, is actually the same species as Shogun Ceanataur. These aggressive individuals inhabit harsh environments like volcanoes and swamps, developing a reddish-brown coloration and tougher shells. They gain additional defense by using the notably tougher skulls of Black Gravios.\\n\\nTerra Shogun Ceanataur, as is normal for a rarer subspecies, is slightly stronger, faster and has more health than the common species.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Water Element\\nSize: 742 cm - 1294 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":270,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":270,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":272,\"keys\":[],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rustrazor Ceanataur\",\"content\":\"The Rustrazor Ceanataur uses its huge pincers and the shell on its back to attack any assailants. From its Gravios shell it shoots jets of water that drill into the ground, and its Glavenus-shaped pincers can shear through steel. This two-sided nature makes it a force to be reckoned with, and earned it the name \\\"Rustrazor\\\". Requires special permission to hunt.\\n\\nRustrazor Ceanataur sharpens its claws with a Glavenus's skull, enhancing their lethality and causing Defense Down. It mimics Glavenus's spin attack using the skull. Additionally, with a Gravios skull, it sprays beams of \\\"water\\\" at opponents, incorporating unique elements into its attacks.\\n\\nElement: Water Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Bleeding, Defense Down\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 742 cm - 1294 cm / Height: Large\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":271,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":271,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":273,\"keys\":[\"Fortress Crab\",\"Shen Gaoren\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shen Gaoren\",\"content\":\"Shen Gaoren (Also called: \\\"Fortress Crab\\\") is recognizable by its grey exoskeleton, towering legs, and the large green-yellow acid balls it generates and hurls from its rear. It uses a Lao-Shan Lung skull for protection and dominates most creatures due to its colossal size. The exact diet of Shen Gaoren is unknown but is presumed to be omnivorous, akin to many real-life crabs.\\n\\nShen Gaoren is relatively passive by nature. It moves about without noticing hunters; when enraged however, it may attempt to attack hunters with its huge sturdy claws or move its legs and pincers wildly.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 3388 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nCarapaceon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":272,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":272,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":274,\"keys\":[\"Carapaceon\",\"Carapaceons\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Carapaceon\",\"content\":\"Carapaceons are monsters with crustacean-like or scorpion-like features, characterized by hard shells, exoskeletons, or crab-like bodies. To weaken them, physical damage is required, and they exhibit signs of internal bleeding through frothing purple bubbles from their mouths. These creatures often resemble crabs, lobsters, or scorpions.\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":273,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":273,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":275,\"keys\":[\"Dire Miralis\",\"Smelting Black Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Dire Miralis\",\"content\":\"Dire Miralis (also called: \\\"Smelting Black Dragon\\\") is a massive semi-aquatic Elder Dragon with a body structure resembling Fatalis. It has short limbs, a long tail, and neck. Its body contains magma-like substance, forming pools at the tail base, chest, and shoulders. The magma flows to different parts of the body. Wing-like appendages on its back, though not designed for flight, serve as cannons to expel magma for defense. Dire Miralis has a frill-like structure on its head and an upturned snout.\\n\\nDire Miralis, being an amphibious Elder Dragon, engages in combat using eruptions of magma-like fluid from its wing plates and fiery blasts from its mouth. Its colossal size allows it to use its limbs and body to crush opponents. The intense heat generated by its body and fluids is capable of boiling the oceans in its habitat and causing widespread devastation to ecosystems, turning them into barren, tainted wastelands.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 6288 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":274,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":274,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":276,\"keys\":[\"Black Dragon\",\"Battle of Destiny\",\"Fatty\",\"The Dark Demise\",\"Black Flame\",\"Fatalis\",\"God of all Monsters\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Fatalis\",\"content\":\"Fatalis (Also called: \\\"Black Dragon\\\", \\\"The Dark Demise\\\", \\\"Black Flame\\\", \\\"God of all Monsters\\\" or \\\"Battle of Destiny\\\" in the Wyverian Language and mockingly called \\\"Fatty\\\") resembles a classic European dragon with black scales, white spines, and a powerful yet thin-bodied structure. It has distinct features like four backward-facing horns, fin-like ears, and six limbs, including muscular wings.\\n\\nFatalis is a powerful monster with destructive fire abilities, emitting streams of fire and explosive blasts. Its intense body heat can melt metal on contact, and its overwhelming firepower can devastate areas and overcome strong defenses.\\n\\nFatalis is physically formidable, displaying immense strength and stamina. Despite its slim build, it wields its whip-like tail, powerful jaws, and limbs with overwhelming force, capable of effortlessly plowing through stone ruins.\\n\\nFatalis terrifies other monsters, causing them to flee, and its awakening is associated with unexplained natural disasters.\\n\\nFatalis is highly aggressive, especially towards humans, and displays intelligence and sadism, incorporating the melted remains of hunters into its hide for reinforcement.\\n\\nThose who wear its armor are rumored to become mind-broken and possessed by Fatalis.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Dragonblight, Bleeding, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 4137 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":275,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":275,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":277,\"keys\":[\"Crimson Fatalis\",\"Crimson Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Crimson Fatalis\",\"content\":\"Crimson Fatalis (also called: \\\"Crimson Dragon\\\") is a variant with a reddish-crimson coloration, primarily on its chest, neck, undertail, and wing tips. One of its four horns is notably overgrown, likely due to prolonged exposure to the Volcano environment.\\n\\nExtremely aggressive and violent, even by Fatalis standards. The Crimson Fatalis' rage is nearly everlasting. The dragon's natural element of lava and its extreme rage go hand in hand. It will kill anything in its path without a second thought.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Dragonblight, Bleeding\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 4137 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":276,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":276,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":278,\"keys\":[\"Old Fatalis\",\"Ancestral Dragon\",\"White Fatalis\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"White Fatalis\",\"content\":\"White Fatalis (also called: \\\"Old Fatalis\\\", \\\"Ancestral Dragon\\\") has a unique appearance with luminous white scales, antler-like horns, and fur along its back and tail. Its head structure is less reptilian compared to other Fatalis. When enraged, it emits a red glow with lightning sparks around its throat and chest.\\n\\nWhite Fatalis can summon red lightning storms and uses its powerful thunder sac to unleash massive electrical projectiles from its mouth. Additionally, it can imbue its claw with red lightning for powerful attacks.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Thunderblightblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 4137 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":277,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":277,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":279,\"keys\":[\"Lao-Shan Lung\",\"Old Mountain Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lao-Shan Lung\",\"content\":\"Lao-Shan Lung is a colossal monster with a copper-red body, cream-colored underbelly, and dark grey spikes on its neck, back, and tail. It has eight large horns on its head, curving backward, and smaller teeth in its mouth.\\n\\nLao-Shan Lung (also calle: \\\"Old Mountain Dragon\\\") is a colossal monster relying on immense physical strength rather than elemental abilities. It can smash through forts and villages effortlessly, showcasing its raw power. Though not using it for combat, it has Dragon Element energy stored in its body, often manifesting as a Dragon-elemental nature.\\n\\nLao-Shan Lung is generally docile and indifferent to hunters, prioritizing the destruction of forts over engaging in combat. It tends to focus its efforts on breaking through structures rather than actively seeking conflict with hunters.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 6960 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":278,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":278,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":280,\"keys\":[\"Ashen Lao-Shan Lung\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ashen Lao-Shan Lung\",\"content\":\"Ashen Lao-Shan Lung is not a true Subspecies but a regular Lao-Shan Lung that has been exposed to volcanic debris for an extended period. This exposure results in a discolored carapace, giving it a muted grey-blue hue.\\n\\nThey retain the city crushing strength of normal Lao-Shan Lung however their bodies are much harder to penetrate due to the ash and soot solidifying their bodies.\\n\\nAshen Lao-Shan Lung is extremely docile, only directly attacking creatures that disrupt its feeding. The creature often takes little notice of hunters, but will destroy any structure which stands in its way.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 6960 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":279,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":279,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":281,\"keys\":[\"Scorching Mountain Dragon\",\"Zorah Magdaros\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Zorah Magdaros\",\"content\":\"Zorah Magdaros (also called: \\\"Scorching Mountain Dragon\\\") is a massive semi-aquatic Elder Dragon with a rocky hide, resembling a walking volcano. It features a turtle-like shell, a beaked mouth, and emits fire, smoke, and lava from its body. Weak points are present in the form of three magmacore organs on its back and one on its head.\\n\\nZorah Magdaros is an immense monster known for its incredible strength and durability. It can easily smash through terrain and fortifications, making it resistant to normal attacks. While generally docile, it can retaliate with powerful physical blows when angered. The monster's body emits magma from vents and magmacores, which it weaponizes as lava bombs. Additionally, Zorah Magdaros can breathe massive gouts of magma and flame. Siege weapons like ballistae and Dragonators are effective against it.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element\\nSize: ~ 25764 cm / Height: Colossal\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":280,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":280,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":282,\"keys\":[\"Kushala Daora\",\"Shadow Upon the Tempest\",\"Steel Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kushala Daora\",\"content\":\"Kushala Daora (also called: \\\"Steel Dragon\\\", \\\"Shadow Upon the Tempest\\\") is a dragon with metallic skin, large wings, and backward-curving horns. Visible wind surrounds its body, and it shows signs of rust on its nose.\\n\\nKushala Daora can manipulate wind, firing compressed air, creating tornadoes, and generating a wind barrier for defense. In icy regions, its storms may induce freezing winds. It can also produce the Dragon element to enhance its attacks.\\n\\nKushala Daora is a naturally passive Elder Dragon, and will only attack when provoked or attacked.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element, Fire Element\\nSize: 1261 cm - 2391 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":281,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":281,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":283,\"keys\":[],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Rusted Kushala Daora\",\"content\":\"Rusted Kushala Daora is an Elder Dragon whose characteristic metallic skin is, as its name implies, is wholly rusted. Aside from this, the Rusted Kushala Daora resembles a regular Kushala Daora.\\n\\nRusted Kushala Daora has a much more aggressive behavior than that of it's normal counterpart. It tends to use more physical attacks such as biting and charges to attack hunters, and stay on the ground more often. Its roar and screeches are slightly different from Kushala Daora's.\\n\\nRusted Kushala Daora uses his aerial turnaround bite much more often normal Kushala Daora, and can immediately attack with a charge or a wind blast after jumping back (whereas a non-rusted Kushala Daora always taunts first).\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragonblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element\\nSize: 1261 cm - 2391 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":282,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":282,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":284,\"keys\":[\"Emperor of Flame\",\"Ruler of the Flame\",\"Flame King Dragon\",\"Teostra\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Teostra\",\"content\":\"Teostra (also called: \\\"Flame King Dragon\\\", \\\"Emperor of Flame\\\", \\\"Ruler of the Flame\\\") is a fiery red dragon with leonine features, a grand mane, large fangs, and backward-curving horns. It has fur on its wings and tail, serving as the male counterpart to Lunastra.\\n\\nTeostra's main threat lies in its mastery over fire. It can breathe powerful streams of fire, create explosive powder from its scales, and unleash a devastating \\\"Supernova\\\" by igniting all its powder simultaneously.\\n\\nTeostra is highly aggressive and will attack intruders ruthlessly, showing dominance in its territory. It can cooperate with Lunastra and even shares a special interaction called \\\"Bonding\\\" when they are both present in the same area.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Stun, Blastblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Water Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 1479 cm - 2610 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":283,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":283,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":285,\"keys\":[\"Flame Queen Dragon\",\"Lunastra\",\"Empress of Flame\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Lunastra\",\"content\":\"Lunastra (also called: \\\"Flame Queen Dragon\\\", \\\"Empress of Flame\\\") is a dragon with leonine features and a blue coloration. She has a prominent mane, large fangs, and a distinct crest that resembles a sort of crown. Her wings are covered in fur. She is the female counterpart to Teostra.\\n\\nLunastra possesses unique abilities involving blue powder that ignites into blue flames upon contact with fire. These flames slowly damage hunters and drain the health of those nearby, even affecting areas that usually don't require protection against heat. Lunastra uses her wings to spread this powder, creating a strong wind that immobilizes hunters. Blue flames created by fire attacks result in additional damage and strong winds. Lunastra can unleash a massive heat wave, causing widespread blue fire and strong wind pressure, quickly draining the health of hunters within its range. Lunastra is the female counterpart to Teostra, and when both are present, they can perform a special bond attack combining Lunastra's heat wave with Teostra's supernova.\\n\\nLike their male counterparts they are quite aggressive, although under typical circumstances Lunastra are known to be less quick to attack, this changes during their mating season however with them immediately attacking on sight.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 1444 cm - 2575 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":284,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":284,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":286,\"keys\":[\"Phantom of the Deep\",\"Mist Dragon\",\"Chameleos\",\"Ancient Phantom\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Chameleos\",\"content\":\"Chameleos (also called: \\\"Mist Dragon\\\", \\\"Ancient Phantom\\\", \\\"Phantom of the Deep\\\") has a purple and white hide, with large, orb-like eyes that can move independently. It has an elongated and elastic tongue for grasping items from a distance. Its wings, colored purple with a grayish-white membrane, enable flight and control over the direction of its poison fog. The tail resembles a leaf, with a curled, spiraling tip. It resembles a chameleon.\\n\\nhameleos can camouflage itself by using electric currents to refract light, making its body invisible. This ability is disabled if its horn is broken or its tail severed. It creates thick fog for protection and can form toxic clouds. The elongated tongue steals items, and it can spit acid blobs, reduce defense, and inflict stamina-lowering fatigue. Fanning its tail produces High-Pressure wind similar to Kushala Daora's wind barrier.\\n\\nChameleos exhibits a jittery and unpredictable nature in battle, constantly attempting to steal items and poison hunters. Rare sightings suggest it is generally peaceful and tends to avoid combat unless necessary.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Poison, Fatique, Defense Down, Sleep, Noxious Poison\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element, Thunder Element\\nSize: 1395 cm - 2811 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":285,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":285,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":287,\"keys\":[\"Abyssal Dragon\",\"Namielle\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Namielle\",\"content\":\"Namielle (also called: \\\"Abyssal Dragon\\\"), an Elder Dragon, combines features of manta rays, deep-sea fish, and jellyfish. Its massive wings exhibit a stunning contrast of black and light blue, adorned with pulsating rainbow luminescence. The dragon's head, with vibrant red and blue tones, showcases luminescent pulses. Dehydrated, Namielle adopts a milky tan color. In an energized state, its body's blue parts glow and pulsate.\\n\\nNamielle's unique abilities involve a watery mucus layer, enabling it to produce high-pressure water jets and blasts. While gliding like a manta ray, it can also spread water to slide around enemies and create disruptions. Limited by its water supply, Namielle dries out if not replenished. Additionally, it can generate electricity, electrifying its body and puddles, leading to explosive steam reactions or massive electrical explosions when drained completely.\\n\\nNamielle is a seemingly passive monster that will only fight back when provoked. Even when threatened, it will initially only try to repel its attacker until pushed into fighting back fully.\\n\\nElement: Water Element, Thunder Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Thunderblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nSize: 1822 cm - 2560 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":286,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":286,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":288,\"keys\":[\"Floating Mountain Dragon\",\"Yama Tsukami\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Yama Tsukami\",\"content\":\"Yama Tsukami (also called: \\\"Floating Mountain Dragon\\\") is an Elder Dragon with an octopus-like body adorned with moss, algae, and plant life. It features four thick tentacles, large whiskers, and oddly human-like teeth and gums. To stay afloat, it generates gas within its body.\\n\\nYama Tsukami floats using unknown gases and has a symbiotic relationship with Great Thunderbugs. It can release burning gas and use exploding Thunderbugs as weapons.\\n\\nYama Tsukami is a dangerous creature, but it may be docile after feeding. The beast usually uses its large size and ability to fly to get itself out of most situations; however, it can become very hostile if surrounded or cornered.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 4137 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":287,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":287,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":289,\"keys\":[\"Kirin\",\"Phantom Beast\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kirin\",\"content\":\"Kirin (also called: \\\"Phantom Beast\\\") is a Elder Dragon with the ability to summon lightning storms. It is covered in scales, has a lion-like face, and resembles a unicorn. Kirin's mane and tail are charged with static electricity, and it has the power to summon lightning storms during battles.\\n\\nKirin summons lightning for both offense and defense, displaying agility to swiftly attack and evade. It relies on lightning strikes and can cover significant distances with ease. But Kirin uses it's horn to gore an opponent or uses it's hooves to strike an opponent like a horse.\\n\\nKirin appears to be relatively peaceful and passive, yet it is quite capable of launching a powerful barrage of lightning attacks on its foes.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Water Element\\nSize: 271 cm - 989 cm / Height: Small\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":288,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":288,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":290,\"keys\":[\"Orochi Kirin\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Orochi Kirin\",\"content\":\"This Kirin subspecies has a dark navy blue body with violet stripes, a black mane with light purple tips, and a larger, pink-ish horn with a spiraling ridge.\\n\\nOroshi Kirin is even more aggressive than its standard cousin. It is able to summon ice shards to defend itself rather than the lighting strikes employed by its standard cousin. \\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: iceblight\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Water Element\\nSize: 483 cm - 989 cm / Height: Small\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":289,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":289,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":291,\"keys\":[\"Shining giant of the depths\",\"Ceadeus\",\"Ocean Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ceadeus\",\"content\":\"Ceadeus (also called: \\\"Ocean Dragon\\\", \\\"Shining giant of the depths\\\") is a giant whale-like monster with a Dunkleosteus-like face, a prominent fur beard, and two massive horns. Luminous organs line its underside and the top of its mouth, changing color from blue to red when enraged.\\n\\nCeadeus possesses immense strength, capable of causing rubble to fall, smashing open large walls, and even inducing earthquakes by ramming its horns against cavern walls. Additionally, it can expel powerful water beams from its mouth.\\n\\nCeadeus is generally peaceful and won't pose a threat unless provoked. Occasionally, it grinds or rams its horns against walls or the sea floor, likely due to the pain caused by the horns growing over its eyes.\\n\\nElement: Water Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nSize: ~ 5837 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":290,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":290,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":292,\"keys\":[\"Emperor Ocean Dragon\",\"Goldbeard Ceadeus\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Goldbeard Ceadeus\",\"content\":\"Goldbeard Ceadeus (also called: \\\"Emperor Ocean Dragon\\\") is a fully-grown Ceadeus subspecies with a lustrous golden hide, a darker brown underbelly, and a more pronounced mane. Unlike the regular Ceadeus, both of its horns are large and symmetrical, overtaking its remaining eye.\\n\\nGoldbeard Ceadeus is capable of firing a current beam that can be swept from right to left, in addition to the usual vertical attack. It is also known to quickly swim to the top of the ruins, so as to fire a sweeping current beam which affects a wide area.\\n\\nElement: Water Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 6037 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":291,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":291,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":293,\"keys\":[\"Blazing Black Dragon\",\"Alatreon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Alatreon\",\"content\":\"Alatreon is a large quadrupedal dragon covered in razor-sharp black scales with a prominent spiked patch on its chest. It has large wings, a muscular tail, a beaklike mouth, and two serrated horns on its head. Its scales may glow in different colors depending on the active elemental powers it is using.\\n\\nAlatreon is elementally unstable, controlling Dragon, Fire, Ice, Thunder, and Water elements. It can shoot flame, ice, summon lightning, spray flammable fluid, and release draconic energy. Its sharp scales leak elemental energy, giving them different properties. Breaking its horns weakens its elemental powers.\\n\\nAlatreon are considered living natural disasters that can cause storms wherever they go and devastate any area that they decide to live in.\\n\\nHunter's Notes: \\\"Known as a symbol of destruction, people fear even uttering its name. It's rumored to control all of the elements, but most, if not all, records of its existence have been burned.\\\"\\n\\nElement: All\\nAilment: All\\nWeakness: Depends\\nSize: 2969 cm - 2105 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":292,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":292,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":294,\"keys\":[\"Jhen Mohran\",\"Peak Mountain Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Jhen Mohran\",\"content\":\"Jhen Mohran (also called: \\\"Peak Mountain Dragon\\\") is a massive monster with a serpentine body, sturdy tusks, and vestigial back legs. It moves by dragging its body or swimming in the sand. Valuable minerals are present on its rocky spine.\\n\\nJhen Mohran is usually calm but becomes aggressive when threatened, attacking Dragonships by ramming and throwing stones from its back. It tends to ignore hunters climbing on its back, prioritizing the Dragonship.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 11161 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":293,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":293,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":295,\"keys\":[\"Hallowed Jhen Mohran\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Hallowed Jhen Mohran\",\"content\":\"The subspecies of Jhen Mohran is larger and has a deep violet ore covering its body, distinguishing it from the common species with a sandy hide.\\n\\nThis subspecies is even stronger and more formidable than the average Jhen Mohran. It can both withstand and cause a higher amount of damage than the common species.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 12361 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":294,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":294,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":296,\"keys\":[\"Huge Mountain Dragon\",\"Dah'ren Mohran\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Dah'ren Mohran\",\"content\":\"Dah'ren Mohran (also called: \\\"Huge Mountain Dragon\\\") is a large, whale-like dragon covered in jagged armor plating. It features spine-like protrusions on its forelegs and back, with a single gigantic, knife-like horn on its face that extends several meters from its head, distinguishing it from its relative, Jhen Mohran.\\n\\nHunter's Notes: \\\"Colossal elder dragons that swim through the Great Desert, smashing obstacles with their spiral horns. Their unique color comes from the thick layer of oxidized metals and other rare minerals that lodge in their hides over their long lives.\\\"\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 11446 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":295,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":295,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":297,\"keys\":[\"Dragon God\",\"Looming Calamity\",\"Wind Dragon God\",\"Heaven's Catastrophe\",\"Amatsu\",\"Storm Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Amatsu\",\"content\":\"Amatsu is a Leviathan with a unique body structure featuring a small head adorned with massive golden horns, surrounded by flesh tendrils. Its pale white body is covered in fins extending along all limbs, with additional pointed fins on its back. Amatsu's small back legs are nearly vestigial, and its front legs are bordered by white fins. In moments of rage, red veins become prominent in its wing membranes, and nearing death, its chest, horns, and eyes emit a faint golden luminescence. Amatsu spends its entire life airborne and lacks significant time on land.\\n\\nAmatsu controls storms and wind, altering the weather and swimming through the sky using its fins. It can summon gales, create protective wind barriers, and induce torrential storms. Amatsu stores water in its body, using it for powerful water blasts. Unlike Kushala Daora, Amatsu's abilities intensify when injured, and it may use lightning from storms to attack. Its presence is catastrophic, capable of destroying landscapes and driving other monsters away, making it a feared and extreme threat.\\n\\nElement: Water Element, Thunder Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Waterblight, Thunderblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 3133 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":296,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":296,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":298,\"keys\":[\"Dark Eclipse\",\"Gore\",\"Gore Magala\",\"Stalking Shadow\",\"Black Eclipse Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gore Magala\",\"content\":\"Gore Magala (also called: \\\"Gore\\\", \\\"Black Eclipse Wyvern\\\", \\\"Stalking Shadow\\\", \\\"Dark Eclipse\\\") is a unique monster resembling a quadrupedal wyvern with dark plates and hidden feelers alongside its face. It has no visible eyes, fanged jaws as part of its external armor plates, and wings covered in jet-black fur. The wings have prehensile claws with opposable thumbs. Gore Magala can cloak its body with its wings when not in combat.\\n\\nGore Magala emits pollen-like scales that help it understand its environment and sense threats via heat. These scales also carry the Frenzy Virus, transmitted through breath attacks or scattered pools. Gore Magala lacks eyes and relies on scales for detection. As it scatters more scales, its senses sharpen, leading to the Frenzy State, marked by increased strength and aggression. In combat, it uses powerful slashes and grapples with its clawed wingarms.\\n\\nAggressive and intelligent, Gore Magala display cunning behavior, including playing dead, and have been observed to hold grudges against individuals who injure them or drive them off. They become more aggressive as they approach the molting stage into Shagaru Magala.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Frenzy Virus\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Thunder Element, Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: 1549 cm - 2201 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":297,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":297,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":299,\"keys\":[\"Black Eclipse Wyvern\",\"Wandering Malformation\",\"Chaotic Gore Magala\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Chaotic Gore Magala\",\"content\":\"Chaotic Gore Magala (also called: \\\"Black Eclipse Wyvern\\\", \\\"Wandering Malformation\\\") is a result of a disrupted molting process, leaving it with a half-transformed appearance resembling both Gore Magala and Shagaru Magala. Its state is unstable, and it will eventually die if left unchecked.\\n\\nChaotic Gore Magala retains Gore Magala's abilities but exhibits increased strength and ferocity. The partial transformation grants it some of Shagaru Magala's potential and abilities, particularly in virus attacks, but it is notably more reckless than its mature form.\\n\\nChaotic Gore Magala is more violent and aggressive than a regular Gore Magala. Its failed molting induces constant pain, leading to erratic, violent, and unpredictable behavior. This makes it a significant threat, even more so than Shagaru Magala. Hunters are tasked with subduing it to halt its rampage and provide a merciful end.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Frenzy Virus\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: 1584 cm - 2165 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":298,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":298,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":300,\"keys\":[\"Shagaru Magala\",\"Heavenly Revolving Dragon\",\"Bright Eclipse\",\"Heaven's Wheel\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shagaru Magala\",\"content\":\"Shagaru Magala (also called: \\\"Heavenly Revolving Dragon\\\", \\\"Heaven's Wheel\\\", \\\"Bright Eclipse\\\" maintains a body structure similar to its juvenile form, Gore Magala. After shedding its skin, it acquires glittering golden scales covering its body, horns, claws, and spiky protrusions. The once-hidden eyes beneath the horns are fully exposed. Its wings transform into golden scaly sheets that, when fully expanded, resemble a star shape, especially when both wings are spread.\\n\\nShagaru Magala, in its adult form, exhibits enhanced physical abilities, increased aggression, and mastery over the Frenzy Virus. It can execute a variety of attacks, including wingarm pummels and dive assaults. Its Frenzy Virus capabilities are more potent, featuring dangerous breath attacks, virus beams, exploding scales, and energy pillars erupting from the ground. In certain scenarios, it can enter a True Frenzy state marked by purple shades, crystalline claws, and an intense aura. Unlike Gore Magala, Shagaru remains in this state until the end of the hunt.\\n\\nShagaru Magala, despite its divine appearance, exhibits a calm and calculating demeanor, recognizing familiar opponents. However, when provoked, it unleashes a feral and brutal onslaught, displaying monstrous aggression akin to a raging Gore Magala. In a constant state of rage, it fiercely defends its territory, easily overpowering apex predators. Shagaru Magala releases an intensified Frenzy Virus to claim territory, disrupt Gore Magala molting, and propagate the next generation. The virus's wide reach infects various monsters, turning them against each other, with the dark aura dissipating only upon the progenitor's death. Beyond encounters in the Heaven's Mount, little is known about this unique and dangerous Elder Dragon.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Frenzy Virus\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: 1564 cm - 2187 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":299,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":299,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":301,\"keys\":[\"Dalamadur\",\"Serpent King Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Dalamadur\",\"content\":\"Dalamadur (also called: \\\"Serpent King Dragon\\\") is a massive, serpent-like Elder Dragon resembling Najarala. It has a snake-like face, large claws, and reduced hind legs with spurs. The body is adorned with hook-like spikes, glowing vents on the chest, and a red-glowing face and tail when enraged.\\n\\nDalamadur tunnels through stone effortlessly with its barbed body and claws, causing tremors. Its attacks can collapse rock formations, and its tongue has a paralytic agent. It can breathe a fire-like substance and summon meteor-like projectiles, though the origin of this ability is unknown.\\n\\nDalamadur resides in the Heavenly Mountains near Cathar Village. Its hook-like spines aid in navigating the terrain, potentially causing falling debris. The Elder Dragon is territorial, violently attacking anything in its domain. It's uncertain if Dalamadur ventures to other areas.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 44037 cm / Height: Colossal\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":300,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":300,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":302,\"keys\":[\"Shah Dalamadur\",\"Serpent Emperor Dragon\",\"Shah\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shah Dalamadur\",\"content\":\"While Shah Dalamadur (also called: \\\"Shah\\\", \\\"Serpent Emperor Dragon\\\") still looks the same as Dalamadur, Shah Dalamadur has a white tone and his spines have changed colours to a red-orange along with the remnants of his hind legs. The spikes on the top of Shah Dalamadur's face seems to be bigger then regular Dalamadur's spikes. Shah Dalamadur appears to be the same size as normal compared to regular Dalamadur.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Paralysis\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 44037 cm / Height: Colossal\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":301,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":301,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":303,\"keys\":[\"Gogmazios\",\"Gog\",\"Giant Halberd Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gogmazios\",\"content\":\"Gogmazios (also called: \\\"Gog\\\", \\\"Giant Halberd Dragon\\\"), a massive Elder Dragon, shares a body structure with Gore Magala and Shagaru Magala, but with larger wingarms. It has a heavy head with red eyes, rows of sharp teeth, and a scowl-like glow beneath its chin when heated. Its retractable wingarm membranes, indigo scales, and powerful tar-like substance make it distinctive. Notably, an ancient dragonator is lodged in its back.\\n\\nDespite its enormous size, Gogmazios is fully capable of flight thanks to its incredibly powerful wings and presumably light skeleton. It is capable of firing a laser-like beam of superheated oil at attackers, and can use its immense size and weight to batter opponents into submission.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Tarred\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 4920cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":302,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":302,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":304,\"keys\":[\"Nakarkos\",\"Corpse Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nakarkos\",\"content\":\"Nakarkos (Also called: \\\"Corpse Dragon\\\") is a massive cephalopod-like monster with glowing yellow eyes, a sharp beak, and blue skin with bioluminescent spots. It camouflages itself with a self-made covering of bones, concealing its face. Its two primary tentacles resemble a two-headed skeletal dragon with skull-tipped ends.\\n\\nNakarkos coats enemies in sticky mucus, shoots it from tentacles, and burrows underground. Adapted for aquatic environments, it swaps tentacle skulls for monster parts, broadening its abilities. Nakarkos harnesses Dragon energy for tentacle beams and wide-mouth blasts.\\n\\nNakarkos, a solitary and voracious predator, dominates its habitat, eradicating ecosystems to feed its insatiable appetite. Using mucus sprays, it captures and devours powerful monsters, adorning itself with their bones for protection.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Mucus, Boned, Fireblight, Blastblight, Dragonblight, Thunderblight, Paralysis\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 3547 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":303,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":303,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":305,\"keys\":[\"Nergigante\",\"Extinction Dragon\",\"Nergi\",\"Nerg\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Nergigante\",\"content\":\"Nergigante (also called: \\\"Nergi\\\", \\\"Nerg\\\", \\\"Extinction Dragon\\\"), a dragon with a bristly appearance, sports constantly regrowing spikes. It has bull-like horns, a primarily black hide with purple and orange accents, and regenerates skin during attacks. White spikes, when broken before hardening, prevent increased damage. Launched spikes extend attack range and require higher sharpness to avoid bouncing. All body parts with hardened spikes trigger a special attack. Nergigante's advanced forelimbs mimic human-like swipes. Hunters can break its horns, front limbs, wings, and tail, with tail severing possible. Breaking spikes doesn't grant rewards, but eases part breaks, while horn breaking yields rewards.\\n\\nNergigante excels in strength and speed, unleashing relentless physical attacks like bites, slams, and dive-bombs. Its rapid regenerative abilities and constantly growing spikes, initially soft and white, provide resilience. Breaking soft spikes inflicts damage, while letting them grow boosts Nergigante's attacks, violently breaking spikes for extra damage.\\n\\nNergigante, fiercely aggressive, escalates its ferocity when injured and attacks without hesitation. It targets Elder Dragons like Kushala Daora, Teostra, and Lunastra, overpowering them through sheer strength. Devoid of elemental abilities, Nergigante is highly susceptible to status ailments and can fatigue in battle, a rarity among Elder Dragons.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: None\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Thunder Element\\nSize: 1626 cm - 2310 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":304,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":304,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":306,\"keys\":[\"Ruiner Nergi\",\"Ruiner Nerg\",\"Ruiner\",\"Ruiner Nergigante\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Ruiner Nergigante\",\"content\":\"Ruiner Nergigante (also called: \\\"Ruiner\\\", \\\"Ruiner Nerg\\\", \\\"Ruiner Nergi\\\") closely resembles Nergigante but with darker scales and carapace. The distinctive feature of this variant is the presence of black metallic spikes interspersed among its regular bone spikes.\\n\\nRuiner Nergigante adopts a distinct combat approach, starting slow but growing more brutal as it sustains damage. Hardened from countless battles, it exceeds the physical prowess of its normal variant. Sporting metallic spikes on forelimbs, nape, and wings, these spikes, while slower to grow, deliver a potent \\\"spike burst\\\" effect causing the Bleeding effect when fully developed.\\n\\nRuiner Nergigante, like its counterpart, is fiercely aggressive but displays intelligence and patience. Unlike the standard variant's immediate attacks, Ruiner Nergigante adopts a more strategic approach, allowing others to do the work before seizing an opportunity for a meal.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Bleeding\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: 1663 cm - 2310 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":305,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":305,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":307,\"keys\":[\"Xeno\",\"Xeno'Jiva\",\"Dark Light Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Xeno'Jiva\",\"content\":\"Xeno'jiiva (also called: \\\"Xeno\\\", \\\"Dark Light Dragon\\\") is a large dragon with an otherworldly, crystalline appearance. It has two eyes, six orange sensory organs on its horns, and frayed, grayish-blue wings. The body glows ethereal blue, with a red-orange glow when enraged. Upon maturing, Xeno'jiiva transforms into Safi'jiiva after molting its skin.\\n\\nXeno'jiiva hibernates before hatching, absorbing bioenergy from dying Elder Dragons. After birth, it wields blue flame-like energy, firing explosive bursts or beams causing Dragonblight or Fireblight. Initially clumsy, it becomes more proficient in attacks, entering a \\\"Critical State\\\" where it's more aggressive but vulnerable due to energy overflow, risking exhaustion.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: All\\nSize: ~ 4509 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":306,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":306,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":308,\"keys\":[\"Red Dragon\",\"Safi\",\"Red Emperor\",\"Safi'Jiva\",\"Sapphire Star of the Emperor\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Safi'Jiva\",\"content\":\"Safi'jiiva (also called: \\\"Safi\\\", \\\"Red Dragon\\\", \\\"Sapphire Star of the Emperor\\\", \\\"Red Emperor\\\"), a large red dragon, contrasts its juvenile form with a conventional appearance. Its rigid, damage-resistant scales are red with dark accents, and it no longer glows unless absorbing energy or in a \\\"Supercritical\\\" state. Sporting numerous spikes along its back, Safi'jiiva keeps its arms close to the ground, giving a deceptive sense of size despite being almost identical to Xeno'jiiva.\\n\\nSafi'jiiva, the adult form of Xeno'jiiva, excels in bioenergy control, manipulating ecosystems and luring monsters. In combat, it deploys powerful energy attacks, explosive blasts, and physical assaults with bioenergy enhancements. Its exceptionally durable scales deflect attacks, and when injured, Safi'jiiva rapidly heals and re-hardens body parts by absorbing bioenergy.\\n\\nIn moments of extreme anger, Safi'jiiva employs the \\\"Sapphire of the Emperor,\\\" an ultimate attack similar to Behemoth's Ecliptic Meteor. While sparingly used due to the energy requirement, hunters can survive by seeking cover behind rock crags formed by Safi'jiiva's attacks.\\n\\nIn its \\\"Supercritical State,\\\" Safi'jiiva becomes more aggressive and powerful, with its hide softening. This state exposes vulnerabilities without requiring Clutch Claw attacks, and the chest becomes a significant weak point.\\n\\nSafi'jiiva is instantly violent and intelligent, attacking aggressively with heightened calculation compared to its younger form. It drains energy from the surroundings without concern, making it an extreme threat. Remarkably intelligent for an Elder Dragon, Safi'jiiva prefers beam attacks from a distance, strategically leading hunter movements. Unlike Xeno'jiiva, it singles out the greatest threat and focuses its strength on them.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nAilment: Fireblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: All\\nSize: ~ 4799 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":307,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":307,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":309,\"keys\":[\"Vaal\",\"Vaal Hazak\",\"Corpse Coat Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Vaal Hazak\",\"content\":\"Vaal Hazak (also called: \\\"Vaal\\\", \\\"Corpse Coat Dragon\\\"), a slender Elder Dragon, features silver scales concealed by a fleshy red veil. Its standout traits include a double lower jaw with long, sharp fangs, yellow spots on the head, red eyes, and sickle-shaped claws on toes and wingtips. It's similar in size to other Elder Dragons like Teostra and Kushala Daora.\\n\\nVaal Hazak, a solitary and territorial dragon, aggressively defends its territory and attacks large monsters. It buries itself in bone piles, charging up Effluvium for a potent attack. Despite having wings, it rarely flies unless mounted. Known for its life-draining miasma, the Effluvium, Vaal Hazak weakens and kills victims by releasing it violently. Agile and swift, it moves at high speeds and leaps considerable distances.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Effluvium\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: 1843 cm - 2589 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":308,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":308,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":310,\"keys\":[\"Blackveil Vaal\",\"Blackveil Vaal Hazak\",\"Blackveil\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Blackveil Vaal Hazak\",\"content\":\"Blackveil Vaal Hazak (also called: \\\"Blackveil\\\", \\\"Blackveil Vaal\\\"), similar in appearance to its counterpart, stands out with moss-like pustules emitting constant Effluvium. These growths cover its head, rendering it blind, but breaking them restores its vision. Unlike regular Vaal Hazak's dark red and silver coloring, Blackveil is characterized by a green and milky-white coloration.\\n\\nBlackveil Vaal Hazak, a passive monster, attacks when provoked using Effluvium for offense and prey detection. The moss on its body can infect both monsters and the environment, transforming the surroundings into its ideal habitat. Its presence is signaled by a thick green fog of effluvial spores.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Effluvium\\nWeakness: Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: 1843 cm - 2589 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\\n\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":309,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":309,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":311,\"keys\":[\"Mother Goddess of Gold\",\"Glorious Dragon\",\"Kulve Taroth\",\"Kulve\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Kulve Taroth\",\"content\":\"Kulve Taroth (also called: \\\"Kulve\\\", \\\"Glorious Dragon\\\", \\\"Mother Goddess of Gold\\\") is a large, lizard-like dragon with a golden mantle covering its body, featuring blocky scales and massive spiral horns resembling lapis lazuli. Without the mantle, its scales are gold and black with emerald-like patches, and it has ram or frog-like eyes.\\n\\nKulve Taroth can breathe superheated air, instantly melting gold and turning areas into fiery death. Initially docile, it becomes increasingly aggressive in the second phase. The goal is to agitate and make it move to the next arena. Once its mantle is removed, it becomes enraged and attacks with full force. If not agitated enough, it may flee. Breaking enough parts may trigger Fury Mode, further increasing its power.\\n\\nElement: Fire Element\\nAilment: Fireblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 4573 cm / Height: Gigantic\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":310,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":310,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":312,\"keys\":[\"Lord of Ice\",\"Velkhana\",\"Ice Dragon\",\"Ice Dragon that Freezes All\",\"Lord of the Tundra\",\"The Iceborne Wyvern\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Velkhana \",\"content\":\"Velkhana (also called: \\\"Ice Dragon\\\", \\\"The Iceborne Wyvern\\\", \\\"Ice Dragon that Freezes All\\\", \\\"Lord of the Tundra\\\", \\\"Lord of Ice\\\"), a traditional dragon with an upright body, features unique crystalline blue scales and a tiara-like crown of small horns on its head. It summons ice to cover its wings, limbs, and tail, with a thin, flexible tail capable of jabbing at enemies.\\n\\nVelkhana uses ore-infused scales to control cold, breathing supercooled fluid for attacks and creating ice walls. It forms icy armor, disperses freezing clouds to snare enemies, and freezes clouds to rain ice. Agile and evasive, it strikes with a lithe, spear-like tail. If its tail is cut off, Velkhana can create a prosthetic using ice.\\n\\nElement: Ice Element\\nAilment: Iceblight\\nWeakness: Thunder Element, Fire Element, Dragon Element\\nSize: 2336 cm - 3245 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\\n\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":311,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":311,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":313,\"keys\":[\"Shara\",\"Earth Singing Dragon\",\"The Old Everwyrm\",\"Shara Ishvalda\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Shara Ishvalda\",\"content\":\"Shara Ishvalda (also called: \\\"Shara\\\", \\\"Earth Singing Dragon\\\", \\\"The Old Everwyrm\\\") has two forms. Initially covered in rocks, it appears bulky with obscured features and hand-like appendages. In its true form, it is lithe with bark and stone-like hide, bright colors, closed forward-facing eyes, crest-like head features, and well-muscled arms with spindly fingers. Its tail has snaking structures, and its body features spikes and markings resembling skeletal structures.\\n\\nShara Ishvalda manipulates the earth with sonic vibrations, creating quicksand, tunneling through land, and inducing destructive tremors. It fires supersonic beams and energy blasts, altering biomes and agitating monsters. Nearly blind, it uses an alternative sensory organ and accumulates rock armor when burrowing, defending itself and attacking with wingtips.\\n\\nShara Ishvalda, discovered in the Everstream, becomes hyper-aggressive when its rock-covered defense is destroyed and persists in the fight even when mortally injured.\\n\\nElement: None\\nAilment: Stun\\nWeakness: Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 2910 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":312,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":312,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":314,\"keys\":[\"Sky Comet Dragon\",\"Valstrax\",\"Red Comet\",\"Argent Comet\",\"Rocket Powered Elder Dragon\",\"Red Star\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Valstrax\",\"content\":\"Valstrax (also called: \\\"Sky Comet Dragon\\\", \\\"Argent Comet\\\", \\\"Rocket Powered Elder Dragon\\\", \\\"Red Star\\\", \\\"Red Comet\\\")is a slender Elder Dragon with gleaming silver scales. Its distinctive wings are fused into a trident-like structure, expelling dragon energy in reddish flames. Fin-like projections line its back, and its avian-shaped head features a small crest, red irises, and blue sclera. The chest has three horizontal gaps used to take in and pressurize air like a jet engine.\\n\\nValstrax achieves high-speed flight by combining air and Dragon Element energy, manipulating wing alignment for various attacks. Its flexible wings enable thrusting, swinging, and directed explosions. Highly durable and maneuverable, Valstrax survives collisions at top speed. The \\\"Around the World\\\" attack involves a fiery descent, followed by a period of fatigue for retaliation.\\n\\nValstrax is a reclusive monster that stays at high altitudes, descending only to hunt. It unintentionally collides with objects in its airspace and tends to avoid conflict, but fights back fiercely if attacked or if its territory is threatened.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragon Blight\\nWeakness: All Except Dragon Element\\nSize: 2267 cm - 2698 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":313,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":313,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":315,\"keys\":[],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Crimson Glow Valstrax\",\"content\":\"Crimson Glow Valstrax has permanent glowing red marks from chest to wings. Its wings, resembling exhaust vents, emit a bright red glow when inhaling air, and dragon energy emanates from its nostrils and torso when enraged.\\n\\nCrimson Glow Valstrax, a unique mutation, continuously leaks uncontrolled Dragon element, leading to explosive and powerful attacks, including cascades of fireballs and a massive Dragon element laser beam.\\n\\nCrimson Glow Valstrax, with its rampant dragon energy, exhibits heightened aggression, attacking anything in sight. Its altered behavior makes it less reclusive and prone to sudden ambushes, dive-bombing from the atmosphere. Enhanced by mutation, it poses a threat level equivalent to Thunder Serpent Narwa and the strongest Apex Monsters.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragon Blight\\nWeakness: All Except Dragon Element\\nSize: 1836 cm - 2551 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":314,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":314,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":316,\"keys\":[\"Wind Serpent Ibushi\",\"Ibushi\",\"Breath of Ire\",\"Serpent God of Wind\",\"Wind God Dragon\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Wind Serpent Ibushi\",\"content\":\"Wind Serpent Ibushi (also called: \\\"Ibushi\\\", \\\"Wind God Dragon\\\", \\\"Breath of Ire\\\", \\\"Serpent God of Wind\\\"), a male elder dragon of the same species as Thunder Serpent Narwa, boasts a sleek body with a spiky, light blue carapace, upward-pointing narrow horns, and wind sacs on its forelegs, back, chest, and tail tips. These sacs, marked by glowing tendrils, allow Ibushi to float by expelling gas through its \\\"gills.\\\" When angered, its eyes glow with red dragon energy.\\n\\nIbushi is a formidable elder dragon that combines physical strength with the ability to control wind. It can fly using wind sacs, expel Dragon element for ranged attacks, and create tornadoes or explosive gusts. Breaking its wind sacs inflicts significant damage, and Ibushi induces destructive storms that alter the landscape.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Dragon Blight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Fire Element\\nSize: ~ 3068 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":315,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":315,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":317,\"keys\":[\"Thunder God Dragon\",\"Serpent Goddess of Thunder\",\"Thunder Serpent Narwa\",\"Lady of Lightning\",\"Narwa\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Thunder Serpent Narwa\",\"content\":\"Thunder Serpent Narwa (also called: \\\"Narwa\\\", \\\"Thunder God Dragon\\\", \\\"Lady of Lightning\\\", \\\"Serpent Goddess of Thunder\\\") is the female counterpart to Wind Serpent Ibushi, belonging to an Elder Dragon species. It has a long leviathan-like body, short hind legs, and a tail. The species features double jaws and various sacs with different properties based on gender. Narwa distinguishes itself with golden tendrils, backward-facing horns, a large golden sac between hind legs, and purple electrical organs that enable it to fly.\\n\\nNarwa employs electricity for ranged attacks using thunder sacs, electrifying its body and burning foes on contact. It releases blasts, beams, and manipulates metal objects with magnetism. As the fight progresses, Narwa accumulates more electricity, intensifying its attacks and causing destructive electrical storms in the vicinity.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 3875 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":316,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":316,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":318,\"keys\":[\"Allmother Narwa\",\"Narwa the Allmother\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Narwa the Allmother\",\"content\":\"Narwa the Allmother develops eight gold orbs in her belly thundersac, elongates several thundersacs and tails to a bright purple, and her eyes switch between yellow and red. Her golden skin transforms into a dark purple color similar to Apex Monsters. Narwa maintains her characteristic upside-down posture in the air.\\n\\nTo attain the Allmother state, Thunder Serpent Narwa consumes Wind Serpent Ibushi's lifeforce, enhancing her control over wind and electricity. This strengthens her attacks, making her lightning and wind abilities more potent. Narwa inherits some of Ibushi's moves, showcasing an advanced mastery of both elements, and the fertilization of eggs occurs during this process.\\n\\nElement: Thunder Element\\nAilment: Thunderblight, Stun\\nWeakness: Dragon Element, Ice Element\\nSize: ~ 3875 cm / Height: Large\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":317,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":317,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":319,\"keys\":[\"Embodiment of Darkness\",\"Malzeno\",\"Silver Duke Dragon\",\"Scarlet Feast\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Malzeno\",\"content\":\"Malzeno (also called: \\\"Silver Duke Dragon\\\", \\\"Scarlet Feast\\\", \\\"Embodiment of Darkness\\\" resembles a European dragon with dark scales, leech-like creatures (Qurio), wings with a red underside, and distinctive features like golden horns and frills. When it drains life energy, its eyes glow, and specific body parts emit dark red energy, accompanied by illuminated Qurio.\\n\\nMalzeno has a symbiotic relationship with the Qurio, using them to drain life force and launch energy attacks. Its physical strikes, including wingtip spikes and a clawed tail, are powerful and acrobatic. The Qurio-infused attacks cause Bloodblight. When in the \\\"Bloodening\\\" state, Malzeno gains extreme agility, teleportation-like movements, and enhanced explosive attacks. Damaging specific parts can disrupt this state, preventing a devastating final attack.\\n\\nMalzeno, once a peaceful monster known as Primordial Malzeno, turned aggressive after a struggle for dominance with the Archedemon of the Abyss. Forced into symbiosis with the Qurio, it underwent a morphological change over 50 years, becoming a feared Elder Dragon that attacks relentlessly, draining life and afflicting creatures with Bloodblight. It was previously believed to be the legendary monster responsible for significant destruction in the kingdom, until the discovery of the Qurio's true master, the Gaismagorm.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Bloodblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 2477 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":318,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":318,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":320,\"keys\":[\"Legend Resurrected\",\"Guardian Knight of Peace\",\"Primordial Malzeno\",\"Silver Duke Dragon\",\"The Demonlord\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Primordial Malzeno\",\"content\":\"Primordial Malzeno (also called: \\\"Silver Duke Dragon\\\", \\\"Legend Resurrected\\\", \\\"Guardian Knight of Peace\\\", \\\"The Demonlord\\\" differs from the regular Malzeno with a more robust appearance, adorned in silver and gold plates resembling armor. In its uninfested state, the Qurio are absent, and its wings have a dark bluish-purple color. When infested by the Qurio, it enters a \\\"Bloodening\\\" state, and further corrosion leads to an advanced \\\"Bloodrage\\\" state. Severely injured, it enters the \\\"Bloodlust\\\" state, turning completely black with fiery orange glowing elements reminiscent of Risen Elder Dragons.\\n\\nPrimordial Malzeno is a formidable Elder Dragon in its uninfested state, displaying superior strength and agility. It fights like a knight, using its wings and tail for offense and defense. It refuses to use Qurio assistance and can stab them out of the air with precision. If forced into symbiotic states, it wields Qurio's power effectively for devastating attacks. In the Bloodlust state, it becomes highly aggressive and powerful, continuously attacking and teleporting until defeated or it manages to purge the Qurio.\\n\\nPrimordial Malzeno, initially a peaceful Elder Dragon, can become ferocious when provoked. It coexisted with humans and is intelligent, displaying emotional understanding. However, it fiercely resists the Qurio and Gaismagorm, viewing them as a threat and actively hunting Qurio to resist their control. Even when infested, it continually struggles against the symbiosis.\\n\\nElement: Dragon Element\\nAilment: Bloodblight, Dragonblight\\nWeakness: Dragon Element\\nSize: ~ 2477 cm / Height: Medium\\nElder Dragon\",\"constant\":false,\"selective\":true,\"insertion_order\":100,\"enabled\":true,\"position\":\"after_char\",\"use_regex\":true,\"extensions\":{\"depth\":4,\"weight\":10,\"addMemo\":true,\"displayIndex\":319,\"useProbability\":true,\"characterFilter\":null,\"excludeRecursion\":false,\"linked\":true,\"embedded\":false,\"position\":1,\"exclude_recursion\":false,\"display_index\":319,\"probability\":100,\"selectiveLogic\":0,\"group\":\"\",\"group_override\":false,\"group_weight\":100,\"prevent_recursion\":false,\"delay_until_recursion\":false,\"scan_depth\":null,\"match_whole_words\":null,\"use_group_scoring\":false,\"case_sensitive\":null,\"automation_id\":\"\",\"role\":0,\"vectorized\":false,\"sticky\":null,\"cooldown\":null,\"delay\":null,\"match_persona_description\":false,\"match_character_description\":false,\"match_character_personality\":false,\"match_character_depth_prompt\":false,\"match_scenario\":false,\"match_creator_notes\":false}},{\"id\":321,\"keys\":[\"Invading Demon\",\"Lord of the Underground\",\"Fearsome Demon\",\"Archdemon of the Abyss\",\"Gaismagorm\",\"Abyssal Archdemon\",\"Dark Abyss Dragon\",\"Undead Monster\"],\"secondary_keys\":[],\"comment\":\"Gaismagorm\",\"content\":\"Gaismagorm (also called: \\\"Dark Abyss Dragon\\\", \\\"Abyssal Archdemon\\\", \\\"Archdemon of the Abyss\\\", \\\"Lord of the Underground\\\", \\\"Undead Monster\\\", \\\"Fearsome Demon\\\", \\\"Invading Demon\\\"), a massive Elder Dragon resembling Gogmazios, lacks functional back legs and relies on dexterous forearms adapted from its wings. Its stout head, adorned with two horns, features a unique split mouth with folding segments. The body has thick ridged plating, spikes, and vents expelling energy absorbed from the Qurio, enhancing attacks and propulsion. The Qurio swarm protectively around Gaismagorm. Enraged, it sheds crystallized Qurio, radiating red feather-like protrusions, and vents erupt with flames when further angered.\\n\\nGaismagorm symbiotically controls Qurio for explosive attacks and energy manipulation. It displays incre